quran[1606]{c,v,t}:
  50,1,Qāf. By the Glorious Qur’an
  50,2,"But they wonder that a warner has come to them from among themselves, so the disbelievers say, “This is something strange"
  50,3,"What! Is it when we die and become dust [will we return to life]? That is a far-fetched return.”"
  50,4,"We certainly know what the earth consumes of them [after their death], and with Us is a Preserved Record"
  50,5,"Rather they rejected the truth when it came to them, so they are in a state of confusion"
  50,6,"Have they not then looked at the sky above them – how We built it and adorned it [with stars], and it has no rifts"
  50,7,"And We have spread out the earth and set therein firm mountains, and caused to grow therein plants of every pleasant kind"
  50,8,"as a source of insight and a reminder to every slave who turns [to Allah]"
  50,9,"And We send down from the sky blessed rain, with which We cause to grow gardens and grain for harvest"
  50,10,and towering palm trees having clustered fruit
  50,11,"as a provision for people, and We revive thereby a dead land; likewise will be the resurrection"
  50,12,"The people of Noah rejected [the truth] before them, as well as the people of the Water-pit of Rass and Thamūd"
  50,13,"and so did ‘Ād, Pharaoh, the people of Lot"
  50,14,"and the dwellers of the Forest, and the people of Tubba‘. All of them rejected the messengers, so My warning was fulfilled"
  50,15,"Were We wearied by their first creation? No indeed, yet they are in doubt about the second creation"
  50,16,"We have created man and know what his soul whispers within him, for We are closer to him than his jugular vein"
  50,17,"When the two angel scribes, constantly accompanying him, one on the right, and the other on the left"
  50,18,"Not a single word he utters but there is with him a vigilant watcher, ready [to record it]"
  50,19,The throes of death will come with the truth. This is what you were trying to avoid
  50,20,"And the Trumpet will be blown; that is the Day of [the given] warning"
  50,21,"Everyone will come, accompanied by an angel to drive him and another to testify"
  50,22,"“You were heedless of this; now We have removed your veil, so your vision is sharp Today.”"
  50,23,"His angel-companion will say, “Here is the record ready with me.”"
  50,24,"[It will be said to the two angels], “Throw into Hell every obstinate disbeliever"
  50,25,"every withholder of good, transgressor, and doubter"
  50,26,who set up with Allah another god. Throw him into the severe punishment.”
  50,27,"His [devil] companion will say, “Our Lord, I did not mislead him, but he himself was far astray.”"
  50,28,"Allah will say, “Do not argue in My presence, for I had already given you the warning"
  50,29,"My Word cannot be changed, nor am I unjust to My slaves.”"
  50,30,"[Beware of] the Day when We will say to Hell, “Have you reached your fill?” It will say, “Are there any more?”"
  50,31,"Paradise will be brought near to the righteous, not far off"
  50,32,"[It will be said], “This is what you were promised; this is for everyone who constantly turned [to Allah] and was dutiful"
  50,33,"who feared the Most Compassionate unseen, and came with a devoted heart"
  50,34,Enter it in peace. This is the Day of eternity.”
  50,35,"They will have therein all what they wish for, and We have yet more"
  50,36,"How many nations We destroyed before them [Makkans] who were stronger than them in might! They traveled through the land. Did they find any escape"
  50,37,"Indeed, in that is a reminder for anyone who has a [mindful] heart or lends an attentive ear"
  50,38,"Indeed, We created the heavens and earth and all that is between them in six days, and no weariness touched Us"
  50,39,"So bear patiently [O Prophet] what they say, and glorify the praise of your Lord before sunrise and before sunset"
  50,40,And glorify Him in the night and after the prayers
  50,41,And listen! On the Day when the Caller will call out from a nearby place
  50,42,"the Day when they will hear the Blast [of the second Trumpet] in truth. That is the Day of resurrection"
  50,43,"Indeed, it is We Who give life and cause death, and to Us is the final return"
  50,44,"On the Day when the earth will be rent asunder for them as they hasten forth [from their graves]. That is an easy gathering for Us"
  50,45,"We know best what they say, and you are not there to compel them to believe. But remind with the Qur’an those who fear My warning"
  51,1,"By the winds that scatters [dust]"
  51,2,and by the heavily-laden clouds with water
  51,3,and by the ships that sail with ease
  51,4,"and by the angels who distribute [blessings] by His command"
  51,5,"Indeed, what you are promised is true"
  51,6,and the Judgment will surely come to pass
  51,7,By the heaven with its pathways
  51,8,"Indeed, you [Makkans] have conflicting views [about the truth]"
  51,9,He who is diverted from it is destined to be diverted
  51,10,Doomed are those who base their beliefs on conjecture
  51,11,those who are steeped in ignorance heedlessly
  51,12,"They ask [mockingly], “When is the Day of Judgment?”"
  51,13,It is the Day when they will be punished by the Fire
  51,14,"[It will be said], “Taste your punishment! This is what you were seeking to hasten.”"
  51,15,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and springs"
  51,16,"receiving what their Lord will give them, for they were indeed doers of good beforehand"
  51,17,They used to sleep but little at night
  51,18,and before dawn they would seek forgiveness
  51,19,"and in their wealth, there was a share for the beggar and the destitute"
  51,20,On earth there are signs for those who are certain in faith
  51,21,and also in your own selves. Do you not see
  51,22,And in the heaven is your provision and all that you are promised
  51,23,"By the Lord of the heaven and earth, this [resurrection] is certainly as true as the fact that you can speak"
  51,24,Has there come to you the story of Abraham’s honored guests
  51,25,"When they came to him and said, “Peace.” He said, “Upon you be peace.” [saying to himself] “Unknown people!”"
  51,26,"Then he went quickly to his household, and came with a fat [roasted] calf"
  51,27,"and placed it before them and said, “Will you not eat?”"
  51,28,"He perceived a fear of them. They said, “Do not be afraid,” and gave him glad tidings of a knowledgeable son"
  51,29,"His wife cried out loud, and struck her face [in astonishment] and said, “[I am] a barren old woman!”"
  51,30,"They said, “This is what your Lord said. Indeed, He is the All-Wise, the All-Knowing.”"
  51,31,"Abraham said, “Then what is your mission, O messengers?”"
  51,32,"They said, “We have been sent to a wicked people"
  51,33,to send down upon them stones of clay
  51,34,marked by your Lord for the transgressors.”
  51,35,We brought out those believers who were there
  51,36,"but We only found in it one Muslim household [Lot's family]"
  51,37,"And We left there a sign [as a lesson] for those who fear the painful punishment"
  51,38,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Moses when We sent him to Pharaoh with compelling proofs"
  51,39,"But he and his supporters turned away, and he said about [Moses], “A magician or a madman!”"
  51,40,"So We seized him and his soldiers, and cast them into the sea while he was blameworthy"
  51,41,"And [there is a sign in the story of] ‘Ād, when We sent against them the devastating barren wind"
  51,42,It spared nothing it came upon except that it reduced it to ruin and decay
  51,43,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Thamūd, when they were told, “Enjoy yourselves for a while.”"
  51,44,"But they rebelled against the command of their Lord, so the thunderbolt seized them, while they were looking on"
  51,45,"They could not withstand it, nor could they ward it off"
  51,46,"And the people of Noah [were also destroyed] before them. They were indeed a rebellious people"
  51,47,"We built the heaven with might, and We are indeed expanding it"
  51,48,And We spread out the earth. How well did We smooth it out
  51,49,"And We have created everything in pairs, so that you may take heed"
  51,50,"So flee to Allah. Indeed, I am a clear warner to you from Him"
  51,51,"And do not set up another god with Allah. Indeed, I am a clear warner to you from Him.”"
  51,52,"Likewise, no messenger came to those before them without being told: “A magician, or a madman!”"
  51,53,Did they suggest this to one another? Rather they are a transgressing people
  51,54,"So turn away from them [O Prophet], for you are not to blame"
  51,55,"But keep reminding them, for reminder benefits the believers"
  51,56,I have not created the jinn and mankind except to worship Me
  51,57,"I seek no provision from them, nor do I want them to feed Me"
  51,58,"Indeed, it is Allah Who is the All-Provider, Lord of Power, the Mighty"
  51,59,"Indeed, those who do wrong will have a share [of [punishment] like that of their predecessors, so let them not ask Me to hasten it"
  51,60,"So woe to those who disbelieve from [the punishment of] the Day which they are promised"
  52,1,By the mount of Tūr
  52,2,and by the Book inscribed
  52,3,on an unrolled parchment
  52,4,"and by the much-frequented House [in heaven]"
  52,5,and by the canopy raised high
  52,6,and by the sea ever filled
  52,7,The punishment of your Lord will surely come to pass
  52,8,there is none who can avert it
  52,9,On the Day when the heaven will convulse violently
  52,10,and the mountains will move a horrible movement
  52,11,then woe to the deniers on that Day
  52,12,those who amuse themselves in falsehood
  52,13,On the Day when they will be shoved into the Fire forcefully
  52,14,"[They will be told,] “This is the Fire which you used to deny"
  52,15,"Is this [punishment] magic, or do you not see"
  52,16,"Burn in it, whether you bear it patiently or impatiently, it makes no difference to you; you are recompensed only for what you used to do.”"
  52,17,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and bliss"
  52,18,"enjoying what their Lord has given them, and their Lord protected them from the punishment of the Blazing Fire"
  52,19,“Eat and drink pleasantly for what you used to do
  52,20,reclining on lined up couches”. And We will marry them to houris of wide beautiful eyes
  52,21,"As for those who believe and their offspring follow them in faith, We will cause their offspring to join them, and will not detract anything from [the reward of] their deeds. Everyone will be accountable for what he earned"
  52,22,And We will provide them with whatever fruit and meat they desire
  52,23,"They will pass around to one another a glass [of pure wine] which does not lead to idle talk or sin"
  52,24,"They will be served by their servant boys, as if they were well-protected pearls"
  52,25,They will turn to one another with questions
  52,26,"They will say, “Before this, we used to be in awe [of Allah] when we were living among our people"
  52,27,Therefore Allah conferred favor upon us and protected us from the punishment of the Scorching Fire
  52,28,"Indeed, we used to call upon Him before. He is indeed the Most Kind, the Most Merciful.”"
  52,29,"So keep exhorting [O Prophet], for you are not, by the grace of your Lord, a soothsayer or a madman"
  52,30,"Or do they say: “He is a poet for whom we await a misfortune”"
  52,31,"Say, “Wait, I too am waiting with you.”"
  52,32,"Do their minds prompt them to say such things, or are they a transgressing people"
  52,33,"Or do they say, “He has made it [the Qur’an] up”? Rather, they are not willing to believe"
  52,34,"Then let them produce a discourse like this, if they are truthful"
  52,35,"Were they created by none, or were they the creators [of themselves]"
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and earth? Rather, they are not certain in faith"
  52,37,"Or do they possess the treasures of your Lord, or do they have full control [of everything]"
  52,38,"Or do they have a stairway [to the heaven] by which they eavesdrop? Then let those who eavesdrop produce a compelling proof"
  52,39,Or does He have daughters while you have sons
  52,40,"Or are you asking them [O Prophet] for a reward so they find it too burdensome"
  52,41,"Or do they have [knowledge of] the unseen so they are writing it down"
  52,42,"Or do they intend a plot [against the Prophet]? But the plot of the disbelievers will rebound against themselves"
  52,43,Or do they have a god other than Allah? Glory be to Allah far above what they associate with Him
  52,44,"If they were to see pieces of the sky falling down, they would still say, “[This is only] a mass of clouds.”"
  52,45,So leave them alone until they encounter their Day in which they will be struck down
  52,46,"the Day their plots will not avail them in the least, nor will they be helped"
  52,47,"And for the wrongdoers, there will be another punishment before that, but most of them do not know"
  52,48,"Be patient [O Prophet] with your Lord’s decree, for indeed you are under Our [watchful] Eyes. And glorify the praises of your Lord when you rise"
  52,49,And glorify Him at night and when the stars fade away
  53,1,By the star when it sets
  53,2,"Your companion [the Prophet] has neither strayed nor is he deluded"
  53,3,Nor does he speak out of his own desire
  53,4,"It is but a revelation sent down [to him]"
  53,5,"He was taught by [an angel of] mighty power"
  53,6,"and of great perfection, who manifested himself [in his true form]"
  53,7,when he was on the higher horizon
  53,8,"Then he approached [the Prophet] and descended"
  53,9,until he was only two bow-lengths away or even closer
  53,10,Then he revealed to His slave what he had to reveal
  53,11,"The [Prophet’s] heart did not deny what he saw"
  53,12,Do you dispute with him concerning what he saw
  53,13,He certainly saw him a second time
  53,14,"at the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary [in the seventh heaven]"
  53,15,near which is the Garden of Abode
  53,16,"when the Lote Tree was overwhelmed with [divine] splendors"
  53,17,"His gaze did not wander, nor did it look beyond the limit"
  53,18,He certainly saw some of the greatest signs of his Lord
  53,19,"Have you [O disbelievers] thought about [the idols of] al-Lāt and al-‘Uzzā"
  53,20,"and Manāt, the third one as well"
  53,21,Do you choose for yourselves males and for Him females
  53,22,That is then an unfair division
  53,23,"These [idols] are no more than names you and your forefathers have made up, for which Allah has not sent down any authority. They follow nothing but conjecture and what their souls desire, although there has come to them guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,Is it that man can get whatever he wishes for
  53,25,"Rather, to Allah belongs the Hereafter and this world"
  53,26,How many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will be of no avail except after Allah’s permission to whom He wills and pleases
  53,27,"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter give the angels female names"
  53,28,"They have no knowledge about it. They only follow conjecture, but conjecture is of no avail against the truth"
  53,29,So pay no heed to those who turn away from Our message and who only seek the life of this world
  53,30,"That is the limit of their knowledge. Indeed, your Lord knows best who has strayed from His Way, and He knows best who is guided"
  53,31,"To Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is on earth, so that He may recompense the evildoers for what they did, and reward those who do good with the best reward"
  53,32,"those who avoid major sins and shameful acts, except for minor lapses. Indeed, your Lord is ample in forgiveness. He knows you best, as He created you from the earth and when you were fetuses in the wombs of your mothers. So do not claim purity for yourselves, for He knows best who is truly righteous"
  53,33,"Have you seen the one who turned away [from Islam]"
  53,34,"who gave a little, and then stopped"
  53,35,"Does he have knowledge of the unseen, so he has insight"
  53,36,Or has he not been informed of what is in the Scriptures of Moses
  53,37,"and of Abraham, who fulfilled his duty"
  53,38,That no bearer of burden will bear the burden of another
  53,39,and that man will not receive except what he strives for
  53,40,and that his efforts will be examined
  53,41,then he will be recompensed in full
  53,42,and that to your Lord is the final return
  53,43,and that He is the One Who makes people laugh and weep
  53,44,and that He is the One Who causes death and gives life
  53,45,"and that He created the pairs, male and female"
  53,46,from an emitted drop of sperm
  53,47,and it is upon Him to bring about the second creation
  53,48,And He is the One Who enriches and bestows wealth
  53,49,"and that He is the Lord of Sirius [a star worshiped before Islam]"
  53,50,"And that He destroyed the earlier ‘Ād [people of Hūd]"
  53,51,"and Thamūd [people of Sālih], sparing none"
  53,52,"and [He destroyed] the people of Noah before them; they were indeed more wicked and more rebellious"
  53,53,"And He toppled the cities [of Sodom and Gomorrah] upside down"
  53,54,"and they were utterly covered [by stones]"
  53,55,Then which of the favors of your Lord do you doubt
  53,56,"This [Prophet] is a warner like the earlier warners"
  53,57,The imminent Hour has drawn near
  53,58,none but Allah can disclose it
  53,59,Do you find this discourse astonishing
  53,60,"and you laugh [at it] and not weep"
  53,61,while persisting in heedlessness
  53,62,"So prostrate to Allah and worship [Him]"
  54,1,The Hour has drawn near and the moon has split asunder
  54,2,"Whenever they see a sign, they turn away and say, “Same old magic!”"
  54,3,"They deny [the truth] and follow their desires, but every matter will reach its inevitable end"
  54,4,"There have already come to them stories [of destroyed nations] that are sufficient to deter them"
  54,5,"which contain extensive wisdom, but the warnings are of no avail"
  54,6,"So turn away from them [O Prophet]. On the Day when the caller will summon them to a horrific event"
  54,7,"with eyes downcast, they will come out of the graves like scattered locusts"
  54,8,"rushing headlong towards the caller. The disbelievers will say, “This is a hard Day!”"
  54,9,"The people of Noah rejected [the truth] before them; they rejected Our slave and said, “He is a madman,” and he was rebuked"
  54,10,"So he called upon his Lord, “I am overpowered, so help me!”"
  54,11,So We opened the gates of the sky with water pouring down in torrents
  54,12,"and We caused the earth to burst forth with springs, then the waters met for a preordained purpose"
  54,13,"We carried him on an [Ark made] of planks and nails"
  54,14,"sailing under Our [watchful] Eyes; as a reward for the one [they] denied"
  54,15,We have certainly left it as a sign; is there anyone to take heed
  54,16,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,17,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,18,‘Ād disbelieved. Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,19,We sent against them a furious wind on a day of continuous misfortune
  54,20,"sweeping people away, as if they were trunks of uprooted palm trees"
  54,21,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,22,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,23,Thamūd rejected the warnings
  54,24,"They said, “Shall we follow a single human being from among us? Then we would surely be in error and insanity"
  54,25,"Has the revelation been sent down upon him out of all of us? Rather, he is an insolent liar.”"
  54,26,Tomorrow they will know who the insolent liar is
  54,27,"We are sending the she-camel as a test for them, so watch them [O Sālih] and be patient"
  54,28,and tell them that the water is to be shared between them; each should take its drink in turn
  54,29,"But they called their companion, and he undertook the task and hamstrung her"
  54,30,Then how were My punishment and My warnings
  54,31,"We sent against them a single blast, leaving them like trampled hedge-building twigs"
  54,32,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,33,The people of Lot rejected the warnings
  54,34,"We sent against them a storm of pebbles, except the family of Lot whom We saved before dawn"
  54,35,as a blessing from Us. Thus do We reward those who give thanks
  54,36,"He had already warned them of Our punishing assault, but they doubted the warnings"
  54,37,"They even demanded that he let them have their way with his angel-guests, so We blinded their eyes, [saying], “Taste My punishment and My warnings!”"
  54,38,By the early morning a lasting torment overtook them
  54,39,Taste My punishment and My warnings
  54,40,We have certainly made the Qur’an easy to understand and remember; is there anyone to take heed
  54,41,"Indeed, warnings came to the people of Pharaoh"
  54,42,"But they rejected all of Our signs, so We seized them with the grip of the All-Mighty, Most Powerful"
  54,43,"Are your disbelievers [O Makkans] superior than those, or have you been granted immunity in divine Scriptures"
  54,44,"Or do they say, “We are a united front, bound to prevail.”"
  54,45,"Soon their united front will be defeated, and they will flee"
  54,46,"But the Hour is their appointed time, and the Hour is more catastrophic and more bitter"
  54,47,"Indeed, the wicked are in error and will be in blazes"
  54,48,"On the Day when they will be dragged into the Fire on their faces, [they will be told], “Taste the agony of Hell!”"
  54,49,"Indeed, We have created everything according to a determined measure"
  54,50,"Our command is but a single word, which is fulfilled in the blink of an eye"
  54,51,"We have destroyed many like you [O Makkans]; is there anyone to take heed"
  54,52,Everything they did is in the written records
  54,53,"and everything, small or big, is written down"
  54,54,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and rivers"
  54,55,seated in honor in the presence of the Most Powerful Sovereign
  55,1,The Most Compassionate
  55,2,has taught the Qur’an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,and taught him speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon follow their precise courses
  55,6,"and the stars and trees prostrate [to Allah]"
  55,7,He raised the heaven and enjoined justice
  55,8,so that you may not transgress the limits of justice
  55,9,"Therefore establish weights in justice, and do not give short measure"
  55,10,He has spread out the earth for all creatures
  55,11,in which there are fruits and palm trees with date stalks
  55,12,"and grain having chaff, and fragrant plants"
  55,13,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,14,He created man from dry clay like pottery
  55,15,and He created the jinn from a smokeless flame of fire
  55,16,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,17,"[He is] Lord of the two sunrises and Lord of the two sunsets"
  55,18,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,19,"He merges the two seas [of fresh and salty water] meeting together"
  55,20,yet between them is a barrier so that they do not cross
  55,21,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,22,Out of both of them emerge pearls and coral
  55,23,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,24,To Him belong the sailing ships raised up in the sea like mountains
  55,25,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,26,Everyone on earth will perish
  55,27,"but there will remain the Face of your Lord, full of Majesty and Honor"
  55,28,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,29,All those in the heavens and earth ask of Him; every day He is engaged in some matters
  55,30,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,31,"We will attend to you, O two multitudes [men and jinn]"
  55,32,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,33,"O assembly of jinn and mankind, if you are able to pass beyond the realms of the heavens and earth, then pass; you cannot pass without [Our] authority"
  55,34,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,35,"There will be sent against you flames of fire and smoke, and you will not be able to defend yourselves"
  55,36,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,37,"When the heaven is split asunder and becomes crimson, like red hide"
  55,38,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,39,On that Day no human or jinn will be asked about his sin
  55,40,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,41,"The wicked will be known by their marks, and will be seized by their forelocks and their feet"
  55,42,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,43,"[They will be told] “This is the Hell that the wicked used to deny.”"
  55,44,They will go round between it and scalding water
  55,45,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,46,For those who fear of standing before their Lord will be two Gardens
  55,47,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,48,Shaded by spreading branches
  55,49,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,50,In each there are two flowing springs
  55,51,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,52,In each there are two kinds of every fruit
  55,53,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,54,"They will recline on couches lined with rich brocade, with the fruits of both gardens within reach"
  55,55,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,56,"In them there will be maidens of restrained gaze, untouched before them by any man or jinn"
  55,57,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,58,As if they were rubies and pearls
  55,59,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,60,Is the reward for goodness anything but goodness
  55,61,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,62,And besides these two there will be two other gardens
  55,63,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,64,Both of deepest green
  55,65,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,66,In each there are two gushing springs
  55,67,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,68,"In each there are fruits, palm trees, and pomegranates"
  55,69,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,70,In them there are beautiful noble women
  55,71,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,72,"Maidens with gorgeous eyes, secluded in pavilions"
  55,73,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,74,No human or jinn has ever touched them before
  55,75,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,76,"[They will be] reclining on green cushions and splendid carpets"
  55,77,"Then which of the favors of your Lord will you [men and jinn] deny"
  55,78,"Blessed is the Name of your Lord, the Lord of Majesty and Honor"
  56,1,When the Inevitable Event comes to pass
  56,2,there will be none to deny its occurrence
  56,3,it will bring some low and raise others up
  56,4,When the earth will be shaken violently
  56,5,and the mountains crushed to pieces
  56,6,and turn to scattered dust
  56,7,then you are sorted into three groups
  56,8,the people of the right – how blessed will be the people of the right
  56,9,The people of the left – how miserable will be the people of the left
  56,10,"And the forerunners [in faith] are the forerunners [in Paradise]"
  56,11,"They are the nearest ones [to Allah]"
  56,12,in Gardens of Bliss
  56,13,many from the early generations
  56,14,and a few from the later generations
  56,15,"[They will be seated] on jeweled couches"
  56,16,"reclining on them, facing one another"
  56,17,They will be served by immortal youths
  56,18,"with cups, pitchers, and glasses [of wine] from a flowing spring"
  56,19,which will neither cause any headache nor intoxication
  56,20,along with fruits of their choice
  56,21,and flesh of birds that they may desire
  56,22,"And [they will have] maidens of wide gorgeous eyes"
  56,23,like pristine pearls
  56,24,as a reward for what they used to do
  56,25,They will not hear therein any idle talk or sinful speech
  56,26,"except the words of peace, peace"
  56,27,The people of the right – how blessed will be the people of the right
  56,28,"[They will be] amid thornless lote trees"
  56,29,and clusters of bananas
  56,30,and shade long-extended
  56,31,and flowing water
  56,32,and abundant fruit –
  56,33,neither ceasing nor restricted –
  56,34,"and mattresses raised high [on beds]"
  56,35,"Indeed, We have perfectly created them [their spouses]"
  56,36,and have made them virgins
  56,37,loving and of equal age
  56,38,for the people of the right
  56,39,many from the earlier generations
  56,40,and many from the later generations
  56,41,And the people of the left – how wretched will be the people of the left
  56,42,"[They will be] in scorching wind and scalding water"
  56,43,in the shade of black smoke
  56,44,neither cool nor refreshing
  56,45,"Indeed, they used to be in luxuries before"
  56,46,"and persisted in the gravest sin [of polytheism]"
  56,47,"They used to say, \"When we die and become dust and bones, will we really be raised again"
  56,48,And our forefathers as well?”
  56,49,"Say, [O Prophet], “Indeed, the former and later generations"
  56,50,will be gathered on a predetermined Day
  56,51,"Then you, O misguided deniers"
  56,52,will surely eat from the tree of zaqqūm
  56,53,filling your bellies with it
  56,54,and drinking scalding water on top of it
  56,55,drinking like thirsty camels do.”
  56,56,This will be their welcome on the Day of Judgment
  56,57,"It is We Who created you; will you not then believe [in resurrection]"
  56,58,Have you thought about the semen that you emit
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or is it We Who are the Creators"
  56,60,"We have ordained death among you, and nothing can overcome us"
  56,61,from transforming you and recreating you in forms that you do not know
  56,62,You are well aware of the first creation; why do you not then take heed
  56,63,Have you thought about what you sow
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it grow, or is it We Who make it grow"
  56,65,"If We willed, We could reduce your harvest to crumble, leaving you to wonder and lament"
  56,66,“We suffered loss
  56,67,"rather, we are deprived.”"
  56,68,Have you thought about the water that you drink
  56,69,"Is it you who bring it down from the clouds, or is it We Who bring it down"
  56,70,"If We willed, We could make it salty; will you not then give thanks"
  56,71,Have you thought about the fire that you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who produced its trees, or is it We Who produced it"
  56,73,"We made it a reminder [of the Hellfire] and a benefit for the travelers"
  56,74,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  56,75,I do swear by the positions of the stars –
  56,76,"and this is indeed a great oath, if only you knew –"
  56,77,that this is indeed a noble Qur’an
  56,78,in a well-preserved Record
  56,79,"that none can touch except the purified [angels] –"
  56,80,a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  56,81,Do you take this discourse lightly
  56,82,"and instead [of thanking Allah] for the provision you are given, you show ingratitude"
  56,83,"Then why [you are helpless] when the soul reaches the throat"
  56,84,while you are looking on
  56,85,"when We are closer to him than you, but you do not see"
  56,86,"If you are not subject to retribution, then why do you not"
  56,87,"bring that [soul] back, if you are truthful"
  56,88,If that dying person is one of those who will be brought near to Allah
  56,89,"then [he will have] comfort, fragrance, and Garden of Bliss"
  56,90,If he is one of the people of the right
  56,91,"[He will be told], “Peace be to you, for being one of the people of the right.”"
  56,92,But if he is one of the misguided deniers
  56,93,then he will be welcomed with scalding water
  56,94,and he will burn in Blazing Fire
  56,95,This is indeed the absolute truth
  56,96,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  57,1,"All that is in the heavens and earth glorifies Allah, for He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  57,2,"To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth; He gives life and causes death, and He is Most Capable of all things"
  57,3,"He is the First and the Last, the Manifest and the Hidden, and He is All-Knowing of everything"
  57,4,"It is He Who created the heavens and earth in six days, and then rose over the Throne. He knows all that goes into the earth and all that comes out of it, and all that descends from the heaven and all that ascends to it. He is with you wherever you are, and Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  57,5,"To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth, and to Allah will return all matters"
  57,6,"He causes the night to merge into the day and the day to merge into the night, and He is All-Knowing of what is in the hearts"
  57,7,"Believe in Allah and His Messenger, and spend [in Allah’s cause] out of what He has entrusted you with. For those among you who believe and spend, there will be a great reward"
  57,8,"Why is it that you do not believe in Allah when the Messenger is calling you to believe in your Lord, and He has already taken a covenant from you, if you will ever believe"
  57,9,"It is He Who sends down clear verses to His slave to bring you out of the depths of darkness into the light. Indeed, Allah is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to you"
  57,10,"Why is it that you do not spend in the cause of Allah, when Allah alone will inherit the heavens and earth? Those of you who spent and fought before the conquest [of Mecca and those who did not] are not equal. They are much greater in rank than those who spent and fought afterwards. Yet Allah has promised each a fine reward, and Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  57,11,"Who is there to lend Allah a goodly loan, so He will multiply it for him, and for him there will be a generous reward"
  57,12,"[Remember] the Day when you will see the believing men and women, with their light streaming ahead of them and on their right. [They will be told], “Glad tidings for you Today: gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever.” That is the supreme triumph"
  57,13,"On that Day the hypocrite men and women will say to those who believe, “Wait for us, so that we may have some of your light.” It will be said, “Go back and seek light elsewhere.” Then a wall will be placed between them, which will have a gate, on the inside of which there will be mercy and on the outside there will be punishment"
  57,14,"The hypocrites will call out to the believers, “Were we not with you?” They will say, “Yes, but you allowed yourselves to succumb to temptations, you awaited [some misfortune to befall us], you doubted, and you were deceived by false hopes, until Allah’s decree came to pass. Thus the deceiver [Satan] deceived you concerning Allah"
  57,15,So this Day no ransom will be accepted from you or from the disbelievers. Your abode is the Fire; it is a fitting place for you – what a wretched destination!”
  57,16,"Has the time not yet come for those who believe that their hearts should be humbled at the remembrance of Allah and to the truth that has been revealed? And that they should not be like those who were given the Scripture before, whose hearts grew hard after the passage of long time, and many of them were evildoers"
  57,17,Know that Allah revives the earth after its death. We have made the signs clear to you so that you may understand
  57,18,"Indeed, those men and women who give in charity and lend to Allah a goodly loan, it will be multiplied for them, and for them there will be a generous reward"
  57,19,"Those who believe in Allah and His messengers, it is they who are the people of the truth. And the martyrs will have their reward and their light with their Lord. As for those who disbelieve and reject Our verses, they are the people of the Blazing Fire"
  57,20,"Know that the life of this world is no more than play, amusement, adornment, boasting among yourselves, and a competition in wealth and children. It is like plants that flourish after rain, pleasing the sowers, then they wither and you see them turning yellow, then they crumble. And in the Hereafter there will be severe punishment, or forgiveness from Allah and His pleasure. For the life of this world is no more than a fleeting enjoyment"
  57,21,"Race one another towards forgiveness from your Lord and Paradise the width of which is like the width of the heaven and earth, prepared for those who believe in Allah and His messengers. That is the bounty of Allah which He gives to whom He wills, for Allah is the Lord of great bounty"
  57,22,No calamity befalls the earth or yourselves but it is already written in a Record before We bring it into existence. That is indeed easy for Allah –
  57,23,"so that you may not grieve over what you have missed, nor exult over what He has given you, for Allah does not love anyone who is conceited and boastful –"
  57,24,"those who are stingy and promote stinginess among people. And those who turn away, then Allah is the Self-Sufficient, the Praiseworthy"
  57,25,"We have sent Our messengers with clear proofs, and sent down with them the Scripture and the criteria of justice, so that the people may uphold justice. And We sent down iron, in which there is great might and benefits for people, so that Allah may make known those who help His cause and His messengers without seeing Him. Indeed, Allah is All-Powerful, All-Mighty"
  57,26,"We sent Noah and Abraham, and gave prophethood and Scripture to their offspring: some among them are guided, but most of them are evildoers"
  57,27,"Then We sent Our messengers in their footsteps, and We sent after them Jesus, son of Mary; We gave him the Gospel, and instilled kindness and mercy in the hearts of those who followed him. As for monasticism, they invented it – We did not prescribe it for them – seeking thereby Allah’s pleasure, yet they did not observe it faithfully. So We gave those who believed among them their reward, but most of them are evildoers"
  57,28,"O you who believe, fear Allah and believe in His Messenger; He will give you a double share of His mercy, and will give you a light by which you walk, and forgive you, for Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  57,29,"[This is] so that the People of the Book may know that they have no power over anything of Allah’s bounty, and that all bounty is in the Hands of Allah; He gives it to whom He wills, for Allah is the Lord of great bounty"
  58,1,"Indeed, Allah has heard the words of the woman who was arguing with you [O Prophet] concerning her husband, and was complaining to Allah. Allah has heard the discussion between the two of you, for Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  58,2,"As for those among you who divorce their wives by likening them to their mothers, they are not their mothers; their mothers are none but those who gave birth to them. They utter words that are abhorrent and false, but Allah is Most Pardoning, Most Forgiving"
  58,3,"But those who divorce their wives by likening them to their mothers then retract what they said, they must free a slave before they are intimate with each other. This is what you are admonished, and Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,4,"But whoever cannot afford this must fast for two consecutive months before the couple have intimate relation with each other. But if he is unable to do that, he must feed sixty needy people. This is so that you may truly believe in Allah and His Messenger. These are the limits ordained by Allah, and for the disbelievers there will be a painful punishment"
  58,5,"Indeed, those who oppose Allah and His Messenger will be debased, just as those who came before them were debased, for We have surely sent down clear signs. And for the disbelievers there will be a humiliating punishment"
  58,6,"On the Day when Allah will resurrect them all together, and will inform them of what they did; Allah has kept their complete record, while they have forgotten it. For Allah is Witness over all things"
  58,7,"Do you not see that Allah knows all that is in the heavens and all that is on earth? No secret consultation takes place between three, but He is their fourth, or between five, but He is their sixth, or between fewer or more than that, but He is with them wherever they may be. Then He will inform them of what they did on the Day of Resurrection. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing of everything"
  58,8,"Have you not seen those who were forbidden from holding secret talks, yet they go back to do what they were forbidden from, conspiring in sin and aggression, and in disobedience to the Messenger? When they come to you, they greet you other than the way Allah greets you, and they say to one another, “Why does Allah not punish us for what we say?” Sufficient is Hell for them; they will enter it. What a terrible destination"
  58,9,"O you who believe, when you hold secret talk, do not do so in sin and aggression, and in disobedience to the Messenger, rather do so in righteousness and piety. And fear Allah, to Whom you will be gathered"
  58,10,"Secret talks are only prompted by Satan to grieve the believers, but he cannot harm them in the least except with Allah’s permission. So let the believers put their trust in Allah"
  58,11,"O you who believe, when you are told to make room in your gatherings, then make room; Allah will give you abundance. And when you are told to rise, then rise; Allah will raise in ranks those who believed from among you and those who are given knowledge. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,12,"O you who believe, when you consult the Messenger in private, give something in charity before your consultation; that is better for you and more conducive to purity. But if you do not have the means, then Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  58,13,"Are you afraid of giving charities before your consultations with him? If you are unable to do so, and Allah has pardoned you, then establish prayer and give zakah, and obey Allah and His Messenger. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,14,"Do you not see those [hypocrites] who take as allies people who have incurred Allah’s wrath. They are neither of you nor of them, and they swear falsely while they know"
  58,15,Allah has prepared for them a severe punishment. Evil is indeed what they do
  58,16,"They have taken their oaths as a shield, in order to hinder people from the way of Allah. For them there will be a humiliating punishment"
  58,17,Neither their wealth nor their children will avail them anything against Allah. They are the people of the Fire; they will abide therein forever
  58,18,"On the Day when Allah will raise them all, they will swear to Him as they swear to you, thinking that they have something to stand on. Indeed, it is they who are the liars"
  58,19,"Satan has taken hold of them and has thus caused them to forget the remembrance of Allah. They are the party of Satan. Indeed, the party of Satan will be the losers"
  58,20,"Indeed, those who oppose Allah and His Messenger, they are among the most debased"
  58,21,"Allah has decreed, “I and My messengers will surely prevail.” Indeed, Allah is All-Powerful, All-Mighty"
  58,22,"You will not find any people who believe in Allah and the Last Day taking as allies those who oppose Allah and His Messenger, even if they were their parents, their children, their brothers, or their kindred. It is they in whose hearts Allah has instilled faith and strengthened them with a spirit from Him. He will admit them to gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Allah. They are the party of Allah. Indeed, it is the party of Allah that will be the successful"
  59,1,"All that is in the heavens and all that is on earth glorifies Allah, for He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  59,2,"It is He Who expelled the disbelievers of the People of the Book [Banī Nadīr] from their homes as the first banishment. You did not think that they would leave, and they thought that their fortresses would protect them from Allah. But [the punishment of] Allah came upon them from where they did not expect and He cast dread in their hearts, destroying their homes with their own hands and the hands of the believers. So take a lesson, O you people of insight"
  59,3,"Had Allah not decreed exile for them, He would have surely punished them in this world. And in the Hereafter, there will be for them the punishment of the Fire"
  59,4,"That is because they opposed Allah and His Messenger. And whoever opposes Allah, Allah is truly severe in punishment"
  59,5,"Whatever palm trees you cut down or left standing on their trunks, it was by Allah’s Will, so that He might disgrace the evildoers"
  59,6,"Whatever gains Allah has bestowed upon His Messenger from them, you did not spur on any horses or camels for that, but Allah gives authority to His messengers over whom He wills, and Allah is Most Capable of all things"
  59,7,"Whatever gains Allah has bestowed upon His Messenger from the people of the towns belongs to Allah and the Messenger, and to his close relatives, orphans, the needy, and stranded wayfarers, so that wealth should not circulate only among those of you who are rich. Whatever the Messenger gives you, accept it, and whatever he forbids you, refrain from it. And fear Allah; indeed, Allah is severe in punishment"
  59,8,"For the poor emigrants [there is a due share] who were driven out of their homes and their properties, seeking Allah’s bounty and pleasure, and helping the cause of Allah and His Messenger. It is they who are the truthful"
  59,9,"As for those who were settled in the city [of Madinah] and embraced Islam before them, they love those who migrated to them, and find no covetous desire in their hearts for what they were given. Rather they give them preference over themselves even though they may be in dire need. Whoever is protected from the covetousness of their souls, it is they who are successful"
  59,10,"And those who came after them say, “Our Lord, forgive us and our brethren who preceded us in faith, and do not let there be any ill feelings in our hearts towards those who believe. Our Lord, indeed, You are All-Gracious, Most Merciful.”"
  59,11,"Have you not seen the hypocrites who say to their fellow disbelievers from the People of the Book, “If you are expelled, we will surely leave with you, and we will never obey anyone concerning you, and if you are attacked, we will surely come to your aid.” But Allah bears witness that they are truly liars"
  59,12,"If they are expelled, they will not leave with them, and if they are attacked, they will not come to their aid. Even if they come to their help, they will certainly turn and flee, then they will not be helped"
  59,13,"Indeed, your fear in their hearts is greater than their fear of Allah. That is because they are a people devoid of understanding"
  59,14,"They will not fight you all together but in fortified towns or from behind walls. Their valor among themselves is great; you think they are united, but their hearts are divided. That is because they are a people who do not understand"
  59,15,"They are like those who were shortly before them, who tasted the evil consequence of their deeds, and for them there will be a painful punishment"
  59,16,"They are like Satan when he says to man, “Disbelieve,” then when he disbelieves, he says, “I have nothing to do with you. I surely fear Allah, the Lord of the worlds.”"
  59,17,"So they will both end up in the Fire, abiding therein forever. That is the recompense of the wrongdoers"
  59,18,"O you who believe, fear Allah, and let every soul consider what it has sent forth for tomorrow. And fear Allah. Indeed, Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  59,19,"Do not be like those who forgot Allah, so He made them forget themselves. It is they who are the evildoers"
  59,20,The people of Hell and the people of Paradise are not equal. It is the people of Paradise who will triumph
  59,21,"Had We sent down this Qur’an upon a mountain, you would have seen it humbled and break asunder out of awe of Allah. Such are the similitudes We set forth for people so that they may reflect"
  59,22,"He is Allah; none has the right to be worshiped except Him, Knower of the unseen and the seen; He is the Most Compassionate, the Most Merciful"
  59,23,"He is Allah; none has the right to be worshiped except Him, the Sovereign, the Most Holy, the Most Perfect, the Granter of Security, the Watcher over all, the All-Mighty, the Compeller, the Supreme. Glory be to Allah far above what they associate with Him"
  59,24,"He is Allah, the Creator, the Maker, the Fashioner. He has the most beautiful names. All that is in the heavens and earth glorifies Him, for He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  60,1,"O you who believe, do not take My enemies and your enemies as allies, offering them friendship even though they rejected the truth that has come to you, and they have driven out the Messenger and yourselves [from Makkah] simply because you believe in Allah, your Lord – if you have emigrated to struggle in My cause and seek My pleasure. How can you disclose secrets [of the believers], showing them friendship, when I know best all that you conceal and all that you reveal? Whoever among you does that has truly strayed from the straight path"
  60,2,"If they gain the upper hand over you, they would be your [open] enemies, and would stretch their hands and tongues towards you to harm you, and they wish that you too would disbelieve"
  60,3,"Neither your relatives nor your children will benefit you on the Day of Resurrection; He will judge between you, and Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  60,4,"Indeed, you have a good example in Abraham and those with him, when they said to their people, “We dissociate ourselves from you and whatever you worship besides Allah. We renounce you, and the enmity and hatred have arisen between us and you forever until you believe in Allah alone”, except for Abraham when he said to his father, “I will seek forgiveness for you, but I cannot protect you from Allah in the least.” “Our Lord, in You we put our trust and to You we turn, and to You is the final return.”"
  60,5,"Our Lord, do not make us subject to the persecution of those who disbelieve; and forgive us, our Lord. Indeed, You are the All-Mighty, the All-Wise.”"
  60,6,"You certainly have a good example in them, for those who look forward with hope to Allah and the Last Day. But whoever turns away, Allah is indeed the Self-Sufficient, the Praiseworthy"
  60,7,"It may be that Allah will bring about friendship between you and those of them whom you hold as enemies. Allah is Most Capable, and Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,8,"Allah does not forbid you from being kind and just to those who did not fight against you nor did they drive you out of your homes. Indeed, Allah loves those who are just"
  60,9,"Allah only forbids you from taking as allies those who fought against you on account of your religion, and drove you out of your homes or helped others in driving you out. Whoever takes them as allies, it is they who are the wrongdoers"
  60,10,"O you who believe, when the believing women come to you as migrants, test their sincerity, although Allah knows best about their faith. Then if you find them to be believers, do not send them back to the disbelievers; they are not lawful [wives] for them, nor are they lawful [husbands] for them. But give the disbelievers whatever [dowries] they have spent. And there is no blame on you if you marry them, as long as you give them their dowries. Do not hold on to the marriage ties with the disbelieving women; ask for repayment of whatever [dowries] you have spent, and let the disbelievers ask for repayment of whatever [dowries] they have spent. This is the ruling of Allah that He judges between you, and Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  60,11,"If any of your wives desert you and join the disbelievers [without returning your dowries], and later you take spoils from them, then give to those whose wives have deserted them the equivalent of what they had spent. And fear Allah, in Whom you believe"
  60,12,"O Prophet, when the believing women come to you, pledging to you that they will not associate anything with Allah, that they will not steal, that they will not commit fornication, that they will not kill their children, that they will not falsely attribute [illegitimate] children to their husbands between their arms and their legs, that they will not disobey you in what is right, then accept their pledge and ask Allah to forgive them. Indeed, Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,13,"O you who believe, do not take as allies a people whom Allah is displeased with. They have lost hope in the Hereafter, just as the disbelievers have lost hope in those who are in the graves"
  61,1,"All that is in the heavens and all that is on earth glorifies Allah, for He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  61,2,"O you who believe, why do you say what you do not do"
  61,3,It is most loathsome to Allah that you say what you do not do
  61,4,"Indeed, Allah loves those who fight in His way in firm ranks, as if they were a solid structure"
  61,5,"And [remember] when Moses said to his people, “O my people, why do you hurt me when you know that I am a messenger of Allah to you?” So when they chose to deviate, Allah caused their hearts to deviate, for Allah does not guide the rebellious people"
  61,6,"And [remember] when Jesus, son of Mary, said, “O Children of Israel, I am truly a messenger of Allah to you, confirming the Torah which came before me, and giving glad tidings of a messenger after me whose name will be Ahmad.” But when he came to them with clear proofs, they said, “This is clear magic.”"
  61,7,Who could be more wrong than the one who fabricates lies against Allah when invited to Islam? And Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people
  61,8,"They wish to extinguish the light of Allah with their mouths, but Allah will complete His light, even though the disbelievers dislike it"
  61,9,"It is He Who has sent His Messenger with guidance and the religion of truth, so that He may make it prevail over all religions, even though the polytheists may dislike it"
  61,10,"O you who believe, shall I tell you about a trade that will save you from a painful punishment"
  61,11,"It is to believe in Allah and His Messenger, and to struggle in the way of Allah with your wealth and your lives. That is better for you, if only you knew"
  61,12,"He will forgive you your sins and admit you to gardens under which rivers flow, and pleasant dwellings in Gardens of Eternity. That is the supreme triumph"
  61,13,"And [He will grant you] another favor that you love: help from Allah and an imminent conquest. Give glad tidings to the believers"
  61,14,"O you who believe, be supporters of Allah’s cause, as Jesus, son of Mary, said to the disciples, “Who will be my supporters for Allah’s cause?” The disciples said, “We are the supporters for Allah’s cause.” Then a group of the Children of Israel believed and another disbelieved. We then supported those who believed against their enemies, so they prevailed"
  62,1,"All that is in the heavens and all that is on earth glorifies Allah, the Sovereign, the Most Holy, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  62,2,"It is He Who has sent among the unlettered [Arabs] a messenger from among themselves, reciting to them His verses and purifying them, and teaching them the Book and Wisdom [sunnah], although before that they were clearly misguided"
  62,3,"And [he is also sent] to others of them who have not yet joined them, and He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  62,4,"That is the bounty of Allah that He gives to whom He wills, for Allah is the Lord of great bounty"
  62,5,"The similitude of those who were given the Torah but failed to uphold it, is like that of a donkey laden with books. How terrible is the similitude of those who reject the verses of Allah! And Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  62,6,"Say, “O you who are Jews, if you claim that you alone are Allah’s allies apart from all other people, then wish for death, if you are truthful"
  62,7,But they will never wish for it because of what their hands have sent forth. And Allah is All-Knowing of the wrongdoers
  62,8,"Say, “The death from which you run away will surely overcome you, then you will be brought back to the Knower of the unseen and the seen, and He will inform you of what you used to do.”"
  62,9,"O you who believe, when the call for prayer is made on Friday, then hasten to the remembrance of Allah and leave off trading. That is better for you, if only you knew"
  62,10,"When the prayer is over, disperse in the land and seek from the bounty of Allah, and remember Allah much so that you may be successful"
  62,11,"When they see some merchandise or amusement, they rush towards it and leave you standing. Say, “That which is with Allah is better than amusement and merchandise, and Allah is the Best of Providers.”"
  63,1,"When the hypocrites come to you, they say, “We bear witness that you are indeed the Messenger of Allah” And Allah knows that you are indeed His Messenger, and Allah bears witness that the hypocrites are truly liars"
  63,2,They have taken their oaths as a shield in order to hinder people from the way of Allah. Evil indeed is what they do
  63,3,"That is because they believed, then disbelieved; therefore their hearts have been sealed, so they do not understand"
  63,4,"When you see them, their outward appearance pleases you, and when they speak, you listen to what they say. But they are like planks of wood leaned [against the wall]. They deem every cry to be against them. They are the enemy, so beware of them. May Allah destroy them; how are they deluded"
  63,5,"When it is said to them, “Come, so that the Messenger of Allah may seek forgiveness for you”, they shake their heads, and you see them turning away in arrogance"
  63,6,"It is the same to them whether you seek forgiveness for them or not, Allah will never forgive them. Indeed, Allah does not guide the wicked people"
  63,7,"They are those who say, “Do not spend on those who are with Allah’s Messenger so that they may desert him. But to Allah belong the treasures of the heavens and earth, but the hypocrites do not understand"
  63,8,"They say, “When we return to Madinah, the mightier will surely expel the weaker therefrom.” In fact, all might belongs to Allah and to His Messenger, and to the believers, but the hypocrites do not know"
  63,9,"O you who believe, do not let your wealth and your children distract you from Allah’s remembrance. For whoever does that, it is they who are the losers"
  63,10,"And spend from what We have provided for you before death comes to one of you, then he would say, “My Lord, If only You had delayed me for a short while, so that I would give in charity and be one of the righteous.”"
  63,11,"But Allah will never delay a soul when its appointed time comes, and Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  64,1,"All that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth glorifies Allah. To Him belongs the dominion, and to Him belongs all praise, and He is Most Capable of all things"
  64,2,"It is He Who created you, yet some of you are disbelievers and some of you are believers. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  64,3,"He created the heavens and earth for a true purpose, He shaped you and perfected your form. And to Him is the final return"
  64,4,"He knows all that is in the heavens and earth, and He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal. And Allah is All-Knowing of what is in the hearts"
  64,5,"Has there not come to you the stories of those who disbelieved before you? They tasted the evil consequence of their deeds, and for them there will be a painful punishment"
  64,6,"That is because their messengers came to them with clear proofs, but they said, “How can a human guide us?” Thus they disbelieved and turned away, but Allah had no need for them, for Allah is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  64,7,"The disbelievers claim that they will never be resurrected. Say, “Yes, by my Lord, you will surely be resurrected, then you will surely be informed of what you did. And that is easy for Allah.”"
  64,8,"So believe in Allah and His Messenger, and in the Light [the Qur’an] that We have sent down. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  64,9,"When He will gather you for the Gathering Day; that is the Day of great loss. But whoever believes in Allah and does righteous deeds, He will absolve them of their bad deeds and will admit them to gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. That is the supreme triumph"
  64,10,"As for those who disbelieve and reject Our verses, they will be the people of the Fire, abiding therein forever. What a terrible destination"
  64,11,"No calamity befalls except with Allah’s permission. Whoever believes in Allah, He will guide his heart. And Allah is All-Knowing of everything"
  64,12,"Obey Allah and obey the Messenger, but if you turn away, then the duty of Our Messenger is only to convey the message clearly"
  64,13,"Allah, none has the right to be worshiped except Him. So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  64,14,"O you who believe, indeed, among your wives and your children are some who are enemies to you, so beware of them. But if you pardon and overlook, and forgive, then Allah is indeed All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  64,15,"Your wealth and your children are but a trial, and with Allah is a great reward"
  64,16,"So fear Allah as much as you can, listen and obey, and spend in charity; that is better for your souls. Whoever is protected from the stinginess of his soul, it is they who are successful"
  64,17,"If you lend Allah a goodly loan, He will multiply it for you and forgive you, for Allah is Most Appreciative, Most Forbearing"
  64,18,"Knower of the unseen and the seen, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  65,1,"O Prophet, when you [believers] divorce women, divorce them with concern to their waiting period and keep an accurate count of the waiting period, and fear Allah, your Lord. Do not force them out of their houses, nor should they leave unless they commit a clear shameful act. Such are the limits ordained by Allah. Whoever transgresses the limits ordained by Allah has truly wronged himself. You never know, perhaps Allah will bring about a change [of heart] later"
  65,2,"Then when they have approached the end of their waiting period, either retain them honorably or part with them honorably. Call two just men from among yourselves as witnesses, and give true testimony for the sake of Allah. This is an exhortation for those who believe in Allah and the Last Day. Whoever fears Allah, He will make a way out for him"
  65,3,"and He will provide for him from where he does not expect. Whoever puts his trust in Allah, He is sufficient for him. Indeed, Allah will surely accomplish His purpose, for Allah has set a destiny for everything"
  65,4,"As for those women from among you who reached their menopause, in case you doubt, their waiting period is three months, as well as of those who have not yet menstruated. As for pregnant women, their waiting period ends with delivery. And whoever fears Allah, He will make his matters easy for him"
  65,5,"This is the commandment of Allah that He has sent down to you. Whoever fears Allah, He will absolve him of his bad deeds and will reward him immensely"
  65,6,"Let them live where you live [during their waiting period], according to your means, and do not harass them to make their stay unbearable. If they are pregnant, maintain them until they deliver, and if they suckle your child, compensate them, and graciously settle the question of compensation by mutual understanding. But if you fail to reach an agreement, then another woman may suckle the child"
  65,7,"Let the wealthy man spend according to his means. As for the one with limited resources, he should spend according to whatever Allah has given him. Allah does not burden any soul beyond what He has given him. Allah will bring about ease after hardship"
  65,8,"And [imagine] how many towns rebelled against the commandments of their Lord and His messengers, so We called them to a severe account and punished them with a horrendous punishment"
  65,9,"Thus they tasted the evil consequence of their deeds, and the outcome of their deeds was a total loss"
  65,10,Allah has prepared for them a severe punishment. So fear Allah O people of understanding who have faith. Allah has sent down to you a Reminder
  65,11,"a Messenger who recites to you the clear verses of Allah, so that He may bring those who believe and do righteous deeds out of the depths of darkness into the light. Whoever believes in Allah and does righteous deeds, He will admit him to gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. Allah has prepared for him a good provision"
  65,12,"Allah is the One who has created seven heavens, and likewise for the earth. The Command descends between them so that you may know that Allah is Most Capable of all things, and that Allah has encompassed everything in knowledge"
  66,1,"O Prophet, why do you prohibit [yourself from] what Allah has made lawful to you, seeking to please your wives? Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  66,2,"Allah has ordained for you the way to absolve yourselves from your oaths. Allah is your Guardian, and He is the All-Knowing, the All-Wise"
  66,3,"And [remember] when the Prophet told one of his wives something in secret. Then when she disclosed it [to another wife], and Allah made it known to him, he told [the disclosing wife] part of what was disclosed and overlooked a part. When he informed her of that, she said, “Who informed you of this?” He said, “I was informed by the All-Knowing, the All-Aware"
  66,4,"You both had better turn to Allah in repentance, for your hearts have faltered. But if you insist on conspiring against him, then indeed Allah is his Protector, as well as Gabriel and the righteous believers, and moreover angels are his supporters"
  66,5,"Perhaps, if he were to divorce you all, that his Lord would replace you with better wives who are submissive to Allah, believers, obedient, repentant, devout in worship and fasting – previously married and virgins"
  66,6,"O you who believe, protect yourselves and your families from a Fire whose fuel is people and stones, and is overseen by rigorous and stern angels, who never disobey whatever Allah commands and do whatever they are commanded"
  66,7,"“O you who disbelieve, make no excuses this Day. You will only be recompensed for what you used to do.”"
  66,8,"O you who believe, turn to Allah in sincere repentance. It may be that your Lord will absolve you of your bad deeds and admit you to gardens under which rivers flow, on the Day when Allah will not disgrace the Prophet and those who believed with him. Their light will stream ahead of them and on their right. They will say, “Our Lord, complete our light for us and forgive us, for You are Most Capable of all things.”"
  66,9,"O Prophet, strive [and fight] against the disbelievers and the hypocrites, and be harsh with them. Their abode will be Hell. What a terrible destination"
  66,10,"Allah sets forth an example for the disbelievers: the wife of Noah and the wife of Lot, who were married to two of Our righteous slaves, but they betrayed them. Their husbands could not avail them anything against Allah, and they both were told, “Enter the Fire along with those who enter!”"
  66,11,"And Allah sets forth an example for the believers: the wife of Pharaoh, who said, “My Lord, build for me a house in Paradise near You, save me from Pharaoh and his [evil] deeds, and save me from the wrongdoing people.”"
  66,12,"Also [the example of] Mary, daughter of ‘Imrān who guarded her chastity, so We breathed into her through Our angel [Gabriel], and she firmly believed in the words of her Lord and His Scriptures, and was one of the obedient"
  67,1,"Blessed is He in Whose Hand is the dominion, and He is Most Capable of all things"
  67,2,"Who created death and life to test you as to which of you is best in deeds, and He is the All-Mighty, the Most Forgiving"
  67,3,Who created seven heavens one above another; you will not see any imperfection in the creation of the Most Compassionate. Look again; can you see any flaw
  67,4,Then look again and again; your sight will turn back to you humbled and weary
  67,5,"We have adorned the lowest heaven with lamps and have made them as missiles to stone the devils, and We have prepared for them the punishment of the Blazing Fire"
  67,6,For those who disbelieve in their Lord there will be the punishment of Hell. What a terrible destination
  67,7,"When they are thrown in it, they will hear its roaring as it boils up"
  67,8,"almost bursting in fury. Every time a group is thrown in it, its keepers will ask them, “Did there not come to you a warner?”"
  67,9,"They will say, “Yes, a warner did come to us, but we denied and said, ‘Allah has not sent down anything; you are greatly misguided.’”"
  67,10,"And they will say, “If only we had listened or understood, we would not be among the dwellers of the Blazing Fire.”"
  67,11,Thus they will confess their sins. So away with the dwellers of the Blazing Fire
  67,12,"Indeed, those who fear their Lord unseen will have forgiveness and a great reward"
  67,13,"Whether you speak secretly or openly, He is All-Knowing of that which is in the hearts"
  67,14,"Does He not know His Own creation, when He is the Most Subtle, the All-Aware"
  67,15,"It is He Who made the earth smooth for you, so travel through its regions and eat from His provisions. And to Him is the resurrection"
  67,16,"Do you feel secure that He Who is in the heaven will not cause the earth to sink with you, then suddenly convulse"
  67,17,"Do you feel secure that He Who is in the heaven will not send against you a storm of stones? Only then would you know how [serious] My warning was"
  67,18,"Those who came before them rejected [the messengers]; then how severe was My response"
  67,19,"Do they not see the birds above them, spreading out and folding in their wings? None holds them up except the Most Compassionate. He is indeed All-Seeing of everything"
  67,20,Which is your army that can come to your aid against the Most Compassionate? The disbelievers are in utter delusion
  67,21,Who is there to give you provision if He withholds His provision? Yet they persist in arrogance and aversion
  67,22,"Who is better guided: the one who walks stumbling and falling on his face or the one who walks upright on a straight path"
  67,23,"Say, “It is He Who brought you into being and gave you hearing, sight, and hearts; little do you give thanks.”"
  67,24,"Say, “It is He Who has dispersed you throughout the earth, and to Him you will be gathered.”"
  67,25,"They say: “When will this promise come to pass, if you are truthful?”"
  67,26,"Say, “That knowledge is with Allah alone, and I am only a clear warner.”"
  67,27,"Then when they see it approaching closer, the faces of the disbelievers will be distressed, and it will be said, “This is what you were asking for.”"
  67,28,"Say, “What do you think, if Allah causes me and those who are with me to die or shows us mercy, who will save the disbelievers from a painful punishment?”"
  67,29,"Say, “He is the Most Compassionate; we believe in Him and put our trust in Him. You will come to know who is clearly misguided.”"
  67,30,"Say, “What do you think, if your water were to sink deep into the earth, who can bring you flowing water?”"
  68,1,Nūn. By the pen and what they write
  68,2,"By the grace of your Lord [O Prophet], you are not madman"
  68,3,You will surely have a never-ending reward
  68,4,"Indeed, you are of a great moral character"
  68,5,Soon you will see and they will see
  68,6,which of you is afflicted with madness
  68,7,"Indeed, your Lord alone knows best who has strayed from His way and those who are rightly guided"
  68,8,So do not obey the deniers
  68,9,They wish that you would compromise so they would too compromise
  68,10,And do not obey every disgraceful swearer
  68,11,"backbiter, gossip-monger"
  68,12,"withholder of good, transgressor, sinful"
  68,13,"coarse, and furthermore, an illegitimate child"
  68,14,Simply because he has wealth and children
  68,15,"When Our verses are recited to him, he says, “Ancient fables!”"
  68,16,We will soon brand him on the snout
  68,17,"Indeed, We have tested them [the Makkans] as We tested the people of the garden, when they swore to harvest its fruits in the early morning"
  68,18,"and made no exception [by saying: if Allah wills]"
  68,19,Then it was struck by an affliction from your Lord while they were asleep
  68,20,and it turned to ashes as black as night
  68,21,Then in the early morning they called out to one another
  68,22,“Go early to your garden if you really wish to harvest.”
  68,23,"So they set out, whispering to one another"
  68,24,“Not a single poor person should enter your garden today.”
  68,25,"And they left early, fully determined to stick to their plan"
  68,26,"But when they saw the garden, they said, “We must have lost our way"
  68,27,"Rather, we have been deprived.”"
  68,28,"The best among them said, “Did I not say to you to glorify Allah?”"
  68,29,"They said, “Glory be to our Lord! We were truly wrongdoers.”"
  68,30,"Then they turned to one another, throwing blame"
  68,31,"They said, “Woe to us! We were surely transgressors"
  68,32,Our Lord may give us something better than this. We certainly turn to our Lord in hope.”
  68,33,"Such is the punishment [in this world]; but the punishment of the Hereafter is far worse, if only they knew"
  68,34,"Indeed, the righteous will have gardens of bliss with their Lord"
  68,35,Should We then treat Muslims like the wicked
  68,36,What is the matter with you that you make such a judgment
  68,37,Or do you have a scripture in which you read
  68,38,that you will be given whatever you choose
  68,39,"Or do you have a solemn promise binding upon Us until the Day of Resurrection, that you will have whatever you decide for yourselves"
  68,40,Ask them which of them can guarantee that
  68,41,"Or do they have associate-gods? Then let them bring forth their associate-gods, if they are truthful"
  68,42,"On the Day when the Shin [of Allah] will be uncovered, and they are invited to prostrate, but they will not be able to do so"
  68,43,"Their eyes will be downcast, overwhelmed with humiliation, for they were invited to prostrate when they were capable [but they refused]"
  68,44,"So leave to Me those who reject this message [O Prophet]. We will gradually lead them to their ruin in ways that they do not perceive"
  68,45,"I will give them respite, but My plan is firm"
  68,46,"Or are you asking them for a reward, so they find it too burdensome"
  68,47,"Or do they have knowledge of the unseen, so they write it down"
  68,48,"So be patient with the decree of your Lord, and do not be like [Jonah], the man of the Whale, when he cried out in anguish"
  68,49,"Had it not been for the grace that he received from his Lord, he would have surely been thrown at the barren shore, blameworthy"
  68,50,"But his Lord chose him, and made him one of the righteous"
  68,51,"The disbelievers would almost strike you down with their malicious gazes when they hear the Reminder, and they say, “He is certainly mad.”"
  68,52,But it is nothing other than a reminder to the whole world
  69,1,The Inevitable Hour
  69,2,What is the Inevitable Hour
  69,3,How do you know what the Inevitable Hour is
  69,4,Thamūd and ‘Ād denied the striking calamity of the Hour
  69,5,"As for Thamūd, they were destroyed by a dreadful blast"
  69,6,"And as for ‘Ād, they were destroyed by a furious windstorm"
  69,7,"which He unleashed against them for seven successive nights and eight days, so you would see the people lying dead as if they were hollow trunks of palm trees"
  69,8,Do you see any trace of them now
  69,9,"Also Pharaoh and those who came before him, and the overturned cities [of Lot] committed grave sin"
  69,10,"each disobeying the messenger of their Lord, so He seized them with a severe punishment"
  69,11,"Indeed, when the floodwater overflowed, We carried you [O humans] in the sailing Ark"
  69,12,"so that We might make it a reminder for you, and that attentive ears may take heed"
  69,13,Then when the Trumpet is blown with a single blast
  69,14,and the earth and mountains are lifted up and crushed with a single blow
  69,15,on that Day the Inevitable Event will occur
  69,16,And the sky will split asunder and will be frail on that day
  69,17,"with the angels on all its sides, and on that Day, eight [mighty angels] will bear the Throne of your Lord above them"
  69,18,"On that day, you will be brought forth [before Allah], and none of your secrets will remain hidden"
  69,19,"As for the one who is given his Record in his right hand, he will say, “Here is my Record, read it"
  69,20,I was sure that I would meet my reckoning.”
  69,21,So he will be in a pleasant life
  69,22,in a lofty garden
  69,23,with clustered fruit within his reach
  69,24,"[They will be told,] “Eat and drink joyfully for what you did in the days gone by.”"
  69,25,"As for the one who is given his Record in his left hand, he will say, “Would that I had not been given my Record"
  69,26,nor had I known anything of my reckoning
  69,27,"Would that it [death] had been the end of me"
  69,28,My wealth has been of no avail to me
  69,29,My authority has vanished.”
  69,30,"[It will be said,] “Seize him and shackle him"
  69,31,then make him burn in the Blazing Fire
  69,32,then tie him up with chain of seventy cubits long
  69,33,"For he did not believe in Allah, the Most Great"
  69,34,nor did he encourage feeding the needy
  69,35,So Today he will have no close friend here
  69,36,nor any food except the discharge of wounds
  69,37,none will eat it except the sinners.”
  69,38,I swear by what you can see
  69,39,and what you cannot see
  69,40,"Indeed, this is the word of a noble Messenger"
  69,41,and it is not the word of a poet; little do you believe
  69,42,Nor is it the word of a soothsayer; little do you take heed
  69,43,It is a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  69,44,If he had falsely attributed something to Us
  69,45,We would have surely seized him by the right hand
  69,46,then severed his aorta
  69,47,and none of you could have rescued him
  69,48,"This [Qur’an] is indeed a reminder for those who are righteous"
  69,49,And We surely know that some of you will be deniers
  69,50,and it will certainly be a source of regret for the disbelievers
  69,51,And this is indeed the absolute truth
  69,52,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  70,1,A challenger asked for a punishment bound to come
  70,2,"upon the disbelievers, which none can avert"
  70,3,"from Allah, Lord of the pathways of ascent"
  70,4,by which the angels and the Spirit will ascend to Him on a Day the length of which is fifty thousand years
  70,5,"So be patient [O Prophet] with beautiful patience"
  70,6,"Indeed, they see this [punishment] far off"
  70,7,but We see it to be close at hand
  70,8,On the Day when the sky will be like molten brass
  70,9,and the mountains will be like dyed wool
  70,10,and no close friend will ask about another
  70,11,even though they will see one another. The wicked will wish he could ransom himself from the punishment of that Day by offering his children
  70,12,and his wife and his brother
  70,13,and his kindred who stood by him
  70,14,"and everyone on earth, just to save himself"
  70,15,By no means! It is a raging Flame
  70,16,that will strip off the scalps
  70,17,It will call everyone who turned their backs and disobeyed
  70,18,and amassed and hoarded wealth
  70,19,"Indeed, man was created impatient"
  70,20,"when evil befalls him, he bewails"
  70,21,"but when good fortune comes his way, he becomes tight-fisted –"
  70,22,except those who pray
  70,23,who are steadfast in their prayers
  70,24,and who give a due share of their wealth
  70,25,to the beggar and the dispossessed
  70,26,and who firmly believe in the Day of Judgment
  70,27,and those who fear the punishment of their Lord –
  70,28,for none can feel secure from their Lord’s punishment –
  70,29,and those who guard their private parts
  70,30,"except from their wives or bondwomen whom they own, for then they are not to be blamed"
  70,31,"But whoever seeks beyond that, it is they who are the transgressors"
  70,32,and those who fulfill their trusts and pledges
  70,33,and who are upright in their testimonies
  70,34,and who take due care of their prayers
  70,35,they will be honored in gardens
  70,36,"What is the matter with the disbelievers that they are rushing towards you [O Prophet]"
  70,37,"from the right and from the left, in crowds"
  70,38,Does everyone of them aspire to enter a garden of bliss
  70,39,By no means! We have created them from what they know
  70,40,I swear by the Lord of the sunrises and sunsets that We are surely Capable
  70,41,"to replace them with others better than them, and none can escape Our decree"
  70,42,So leave them to engage in their falsehood and amuse themselves until they meet their Day which they are promised
  70,43,the Day when they will rush out of their graves as if they are racing towards a goal
  70,44,with their eyes downcast and overwhelmed with disgrace. That is the Day that they were promised
  71,1,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people, “Warn your people before there comes to them a painful punishment.”"
  71,2,"He said: “O my people, indeed I am a clear warner to you"
  71,3,"that you worship Allah and fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive you some of your sins and grant you respite until an appointed term. Indeed, when Allah’s appointed term comes, it cannot be delayed, if you only knew!”"
  71,5,"He said, “My Lord, I have surely called my people night and day"
  71,6,but my call only drove them further away
  71,7,"Every time I call them so that You may forgive them, they thrust their fingers into their ears and cover their faces with their garments, and persist in obstinacy and grow extremely arrogant"
  71,8,Then I called them openly
  71,9,then I addressed them in public and in private
  71,10,"I said, ‘Seek forgiveness from your Lord. Indeed, He is Most Forgiving"
  71,11,He will shower you with abundant rain from the sky
  71,12,"and He will give you wealth and children, and bestow upon you gardens and rivers"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you do not fear the Majesty of Allah
  71,14,when He has created you in stages
  71,15,"Do you not see how Allah has created seven heavens, one above another"
  71,16,and has placed the moon therein as a light and the sun as a burning lamp
  71,17,Allah has produced you from the earth like a plant
  71,18,"then He will return you into it, and then will bring you out again"
  71,19,Allah has made the earth wide spread for you
  71,20,so that you may tread its spacious paths.’”
  71,21,"Noah said, “My Lord, they have disobeyed me and followed those whose wealth and children did not increase them except in loss"
  71,22,They have contrived a mighty plot
  71,23,"They said, ‘Do not abandon your gods; and do not abandon Wadd, Suwā‘, Yaghūth, Ya‘ūq, and Nasr.’"
  71,24,"They have led many astray. So [O Lord], do not increase the wrongdoers except in error.”"
  71,25,"Because of their sins they were drowned and then were cast into the Fire, and they did not find any helpers against Allah"
  71,26,"Noah said, “My Lord, do not leave on earth a single disbeliever"
  71,27,"For if You leave them, they will surely lead Your slaves astray and beget none but wicked disbelievers"
  71,28,"My Lord, forgive me and my parents, and whoever enters my house as a believer, and all the believing men and women, and do not increase the wrongdoers except in ruin.”"
  72,1,"Say, “It has been revealed to me that a group of jinn listened [to the Qur’an,] and they said, ‘Indeed, we have heard a wondrous recitation"
  72,2,"that guides to the right way, so we have believed in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord"
  72,3,And that He – our exalted and glorified Lord – has neither taken a wife nor a child
  72,4,"and that the fool among us [Satan] used to say outrageous things about Allah"
  72,5,although we thought that humans and jinn would never tell lies about Allah
  72,6,"And there were some men who used to seek refuge with some jinn, but they only increased them in burden"
  72,7,"They thought, just like you [jinn] thought that Allah would never send any messenger"
  72,8,We have sought to reach the heaven but found it filled with stern guards and flaming fire
  72,9,"We used to take up positions there for eavesdropping, but now anyone who eavesdrops will find a flaming fire waiting for him"
  72,10,"We do not know whether evil is intended for those on earth, or their Lord intends good for them"
  72,11,"Among us are some who are righteous and some who are otherwise, for we follow divergent ways"
  72,12,"We have realized that we can never escape Allah on earth, nor can we ever escape Him by fleeing"
  72,13,"When we heard the guidance [of the Qur’an], we believed in it. Whoever believes in his Lord will have no fear of curtailment [from his reward] or injustice"
  72,14,Among us are some who are Muslims and some who are deviant. Those who accepted Islam have sought the true guidance
  72,15,"but those who are deviant, they will be fuel for Hell.’”"
  72,16,"“If they had remained steadfast on the right way, We would have given them abundant rain"
  72,17,"as a test for them. But whoever turns away from the remembrance of his Lord, He will make him suffer an arduous punishment"
  72,18,"The mosques are for Allah alone, so do not supplicate anyone along with Allah"
  72,19,"Yet when the slave of Allah stood up supplicating Him, they swarmed around him.”"
  72,20,"Say [O Prophet], “I only supplicate my Lord and I do not associate anyone with Him.”"
  72,21,"Say, “I have no power to harm or benefit you.”"
  72,22,"Say, “None can ever protect me from Allah [if I should disobey Him], nor can I ever find a refuge other than Him"
  72,23,"I only convey what I receive from Allah and His messages.” And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger will certainly be in the Fire of Hell, abiding therein forever"
  72,24,"Until when they see what they were promised, they will realize who is weaker in helpers and fewer in number"
  72,25,"Say, “I do not know if what you are promised is near or my Lord has appointed a distant time for it"
  72,26,"[He is] Knower of the unseen, He does not reveal His unseen to anyone"
  72,27,"except the messenger whom He chooses, then He appoints angel-guards before him and behind him"
  72,28,"to ensure that the messengers fully conveyed the messages of their Lord. He encompasses in His knowledge all about them, and keeps count of all things.”"
  73,1,O you the enwrapped one
  73,2,Stand up in prayer at night except a little
  73,3,"half of it, or a little less"
  73,4,"or a little more, and recite the Qur’an at a measured pace"
  73,5,We will send down upon you a heavy revelation
  73,6,"Indeed, prayer at night is more effective and more conducive to proper recitation"
  73,7,"In daytime, you have plenty of time for your worldly matters"
  73,8,"And remember the Name of your Lord, and devote yourself completely to Him"
  73,9,"[He is] Lord of the east and the west; none has the right to be worshiped except Him, so take Him as Disposer of your affairs"
  73,10,"Bear patiently what they say, and avoid them in a gracious manner"
  73,11,"Leave to Me the deniers who are having a life of luxury, and bear with them for a little while"
  73,12,"Indeed, We have heavy shackles and a Blazing Fire"
  73,13,"and food that chokes, and a painful punishment"
  73,14,"on the Day when the earth and the mountains will convulse, and the mountains will be like dunes of loose sand"
  73,15,"Indeed, We have sent to you a Messenger to be a witness over you, just as We sent to Pharaoh a messenger"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the messenger, so We seized him with a severe punishment"
  73,17,"If you disbelieve, then how will you protect yourselves against a Day that will turn children’s hair gray"
  73,18,It will cause the sky to break asunder. His promise will certainly be fulfilled
  73,19,"Indeed, this is a reminder; so whoever wills may take a way to his Lord"
  73,20,"Indeed, your Lord knows that you [O Prophet] stand up in prayer for nearly two-thirds of the night, or half of it, or one-third of it, as do others among your companions. Allah determines the night and the day; He knows that you [Muslims] cannot keep an accurate count of it, so He pardoned you. Recite then as much of the Qur’an as is easy for you [in the night prayers]. He knows that there are some among you who will be ill, and others traveling in the land, seeking the grace of Allah, and others fighting in Allah’s way. So recite as much of it as is easy for you; establish prayer and give zakah; and lend to Allah a goodly loan. Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you will find it with Allah, much better in condition and much greater in reward. And seek forgiveness of Allah, for indeed Allah is All-Forgiving, Most-Merciful"
  74,1,"O you covered [in your cloak]"
  74,2,arise and warn
  74,3,and proclaim the greatness of your Lord
  74,4,and purify your garments
  74,5,and shun idol worshiping
  74,6,and do not do a favor for a greater return
  74,7,and be patient for the sake of your Lord
  74,8,When the Trumpet is sounded
  74,9,that Day will be a difficult day
  74,10,not easy for the disbelievers
  74,11,Leave me alone to deal with the one whom I created
  74,12,and gave him abundant wealth
  74,13,and sons by his side
  74,14,and gave him a life of comfort and power
  74,15,yet he aspires that I should give him more
  74,16,By no means! For he has been stubborn against Our verses
  74,17,I will subject him to an unbearable punishment
  74,18,"For he reflected and plotted [against the Qur’an]"
  74,19,"May he perish, how he plotted"
  74,20,"Again, may he perish, how he plotted"
  74,21,Then he looked around
  74,22,then he frowned and scowled
  74,23,then turned away with arrogance
  74,24,"then said, “This is nothing but magic from the past"
  74,25,This is nothing but the words of a man.”
  74,26,Soon I will make him burn in the Scorching Fire
  74,27,How do you know what Scorching Fire is
  74,28,It leaves nothing and spares no one
  74,29,scorching the skin
  74,30,"It is overseen by nineteen [angels]"
  74,31,"We have only appointed angels as keepers of the Fire, and We have only made their number as a test for the disbelievers, so that those who were given the Scripture may have certainty and the believers may increase in faith; and neither those who were given the Scripture nor the believers may have any doubts; and so that those [hypocrites] in whose hearts is sickness and the disbelievers may say, “What does Allah mean by this number?” Thus Allah causes to stray whom He wills and guides whom He wills, and none knows the soldiers of your Lord but He. This is but a reminder to mankind"
  74,32,No indeed! By the moon
  74,33,and by the night when it departs
  74,34,and by the dawn when it brightens
  74,35,Hellfire is indeed one of the greatest matters
  74,36,a warning to mankind
  74,37,to whoever among you chooses to advance or regress
  74,38,Every soul is held in pledge for its deeds
  74,39,except the People of the Right
  74,40,"who will be in gardens, asking one another"
  74,41,about the wicked
  74,42,“What brought you to Hell?”
  74,43,"They will say, “We were not among those who prayed"
  74,44,nor did we feed the poor
  74,45,and we indulged in falsehood along with those who indulged in it
  74,46,and we denied the Day of Judgment
  74,47,"until the certainty [of death] came to us.”"
  74,48,So the intercession of intercessors will not benefit them
  74,49,Then what is the matter with them that they turn away from the Reminder
  74,50,as if they were terrified wild asses
  74,51,fleeing from a lion
  74,52,"In fact, each one of them desires that open [divine] letters be sent to each of them"
  74,53,By no means! They rather do not fear the Hereafter
  74,54,"No indeed! This [Qur’an] is a reminder"
  74,55,So whoever wills may take heed
  74,56,But they will not take heed unless Allah so wills. He is most worthy to be feared and most worthy to forgive
  75,1,I swear by the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,and I swear by the self-reproaching soul
  75,3,Does man think that We cannot reassemble his bones
  75,4,"In fact, We are able to restore even his very fingertips"
  75,5,But man desires to persists in his evil ways
  75,6,"and asks [mockingly], “When is the Day of Resurrection?”"
  75,7,But when eyes are dazzled
  75,8,and the moon is darkened
  75,9,and the sun and the moon are brought together
  75,10,"on that Day man will say, “Where is the escape?”"
  75,11,No indeed! There will be no refuge
  75,12,On that Day all will end up before your Lord
  75,13,On that Day man will be informed of what he has sent forth and left behind
  75,14,"In fact, man will be a witness against himself"
  75,15,despite the excuses he may put forward
  75,16,"Do not move your tongue [O Prophet] in haste trying to memorize it"
  75,17,It is upon Us to make you memorize and recite it
  75,18,"Then when We recite it [through Gabriel], follow its recitation attentively"
  75,19,then it is upon Us to explain its meanings
  75,20,"No indeed! You [people] love this fleeting world"
  75,21,and neglect the Hereafter
  75,22,On that Day some faces will be bright
  75,23,looking at their Lord
  75,24,"And on that Day, some faces will be gloomy"
  75,25,knowing that a crushing calamity will befall them
  75,26,"Indeed, when the soul reaches the throat"
  75,27,"and it is said, “Is there any healer?”"
  75,28,And he realizes that it is time to depart
  75,29,"when legs are brought together [in a shroud]"
  75,30,"on that Day, he will be driven to your Lord"
  75,31,He neither believed nor prayed
  75,32,rather he denied and turned away
  75,33,then went swaggering to his people
  75,34,"Woe to you [O man], and woe"
  75,35,"Again, woe to you, and woe"
  75,36,Does man think that he will be left neglected
  75,37,Was he not once a drop of semen emitted
  75,38,"then he became a clinging clot, then He created him and perfected his form"
  75,39,"and made from him both genders, male and female"
  75,40,Is not He able to bring the dead back to life
  76,1,"Was there not a period of time when man was not a thing [even] mentioned"
  76,2,"Indeed, We created man from a drop of mixed fluids, in order to test him. So We gave him hearing and sight"
  76,3,"Indeed, We showed him the way, whether he is grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"We have surely prepared for the disbelievers chains, shackles, and a Blazing Fire"
  76,5,"Indeed, the righteous will drink from a cup [of wine] flavored with camphor"
  76,6,"a spring from which Allah’s slaves will drink, which will flow as they wish"
  76,7,They fulfill their vows and fear a Day whose evil will spread far and wide
  76,8,"and they give food, despite their love for it, to the needy, the orphans, and the captives"
  76,9,"[saying to themselves] “We feed you only for the sake of Allah; we seek from you neither reward nor gratitude"
  76,10,We fear from our Lord a grim and distressful Day.”
  76,11,"So Allah will protect them from the evil of that Day, and will grant them radiance and delight"
  76,12,and will reward them for their perseverance with Paradise and garments of silk
  76,13,They will recline therein on adorned couches; neither feeling scorching heat nor freezing cold
  76,14,"with shady branches spread above them, and clusters of fruit will be made within their reach"
  76,15,They will be served frequently with silver vessels and crystal cups
  76,16,"crystalline goblets of silver, filled precisely as desired"
  76,17,"They will be given a glass [of wine] flavored with ginger"
  76,18,from a spring therein called Salsabīl
  76,19,"They will be served by eternal young boys; if you see them, you would think that they are scattered pearls"
  76,20,"If you were to look around, you would see bliss and a vast dominion"
  76,21,"They will be dressed in garments of fine green silk and rich brocade, and will be adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a pure drink"
  76,22,"[And they will be told,] “Indeed, this is your reward, and your efforts have been appreciated.”"
  76,23,"Indeed, it is We Who have sent down the Qur’an to you in stages"
  76,24,"So be patient with your Lord’s decree, and do not obey any sinner or disbeliever from among them"
  76,25,And remember the Name of your Lord morning and evening
  76,26,"and prostrate to Him at night, and glorify Him at length by night"
  76,27,"Indeed, these [pagans] love this fleeting life and pay no heed to a heavy Day ahead of them"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them and strengthened their build. If We will, We can replace them with others like them"
  76,29,"Indeed, this is a reminder; so let anyone who wills may take a way to his Lord"
  76,30,"But you cannot will unless Allah wills. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  76,31,"He admits whom He wills into His mercy, but for the wrongdoers He has prepared a painful punishment"
  77,1,"By those [winds] sent forth in succession"
  77,2,those that blow violently
  77,3,"and scatter [rainclouds] far and wide"
  77,4,"And by those [angels] who bring criterion"
  77,5,and those who deliver revelation
  77,6,leaving no excuse or giving warning –
  77,7,what you are promised will surely come to pass
  77,8,So when the stars are extinguished
  77,9,and when the sky is split apart
  77,10,and when the mountains are blown away
  77,11,and when the messengers are summoned
  77,12,until which Day has all this been postponed
  77,13,Until the Day of Judgment
  77,14,How do you know what the Day of Judgment is
  77,15,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,16,Did We not destroy the earlier nations
  77,17,Then We will do likewise to the later ones
  77,18,This is how We deal with the wicked
  77,19,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,20,Did We not create you from a worthless fluid
  77,21,then We placed it in a secure repository
  77,22,for a determined period
  77,23,For We determined it; How excellently We determine
  77,24,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,25,Have We not made the earth a receptacle
  77,26,for the living and the dead
  77,27,"and placed therein firm towering mountains, and given you fresh water to drink"
  77,28,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,29,"[They will be told,] “Proceed to that [Fire] which you used to deny"
  77,30,"Proceed to the shadow [of smoke] ascending in three columns"
  77,31,that provides neither shade nor protection from the flames
  77,32,"Indeed, it [Hell] throws up sparks as big as castles"
  77,33,as if they were tawny camels
  77,34,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,35,On that Day they won’t speak
  77,36,nor will they be allowed to make excuses
  77,37,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,38,"[They will be told,] “This is the Day of Judgment: We have gathered you along with the earlier generations"
  77,39,"So if you have any scheme, then plot it against Me.”"
  77,40,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,41,"Indeed, the righteous will be amid shades and springs"
  77,42,and will have whatever fruit they desire
  77,43,"[They will be told,] “Eat and drink joyfully, as a reward for what you used to do.”"
  77,44,This is how We reward those who do good
  77,45,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,46,“Eat and enjoy yourselves for a while; you are truly wicked.”
  77,47,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,48,"When it is said to them, “Bow [in prayer]”, they do not bow"
  77,49,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,50,"In which message after this [Qur’an] will they believe"
  78,1,About what are they asking one another
  78,2,About the momentous news
  78,3,about which they differ
  78,4,No indeed; they will come to know
  78,5,Again no; they will come to know
  78,6,Have We not made the earth a resting place
  78,7,And the mountains as stakes
  78,8,and created you in pairs
  78,9,and made your sleep for rest
  78,10,and made the night a covering
  78,11,and made the day for seeking livelihood
  78,12,and built above you seven mighty heavens
  78,13,and made therein a blazing lamp
  78,14,and sent down from the rainclouds abundant water
  78,15,so that We may produce thereby grains and vegetation
  78,16,and gardens with dense foliage
  78,17,"Indeed, the Day of Judgment is a time appointed"
  78,18,"the Day when the Trumpet will be blown, you will come forth in crowds"
  78,19,and the sky will be opened up and will become gateways
  78,20,"and the mountains will vanish, becoming like a mirage"
  78,21,"Indeed, Hell is lying in wait"
  78,22,a resort for the transgressors
  78,23,wherein they will abide for endless ages
  78,24,They will neither taste therein any coolness nor any drink
  78,25,except scalding water and discharge of wounds
  78,26,a fitting recompense
  78,27,"Indeed, they did not expect a reckoning"
  78,28,and utterly rejected Our verses
  78,29,But We have enumerated everything in a record
  78,30,"So taste [the punishment], for We will not increase you except in torment.”"
  78,31,"Indeed, the righteous will have salvation"
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,and full-bosomed maidens of equal age
  78,34,"and a full cup [of wine]"
  78,35,They will not hear therein vain talk or lies –
  78,36,a reward and a generous gift from your Lord
  78,37,"[from] the Lord of the heavens and earth and all that is between them, the Most Compassionate; none will dare to speak to Him"
  78,38,"On the Day when the Spirit and the angels will stand in rows; none will dare to speak, except those to whom the Most Compassionate granted permission, and they will only speak the truth"
  78,39,That Day is sure to come. So whoever wills may seek a path leading to his Lord
  78,40,"Indeed, We have warned you of an imminent punishment on the Day when everyone will see what his hands have sent forth, and the disbeliever will say, “Oh, I wish that I were dust!”"
  79,1,"By those who pull out [evil souls] harshly"
  79,2,"and by those who draw out [good souls] gently"
  79,3,and by those who glide swiftly
  79,4,and those who overtake one another as in a race
  79,5,"and those who carry out the command [of Allah]"
  79,6,"on the Day when the earth convulses [by the first Blast]"
  79,7,followed by the second Blast
  79,8,hearts will be pounding on that Day
  79,9,and their eyes will be downcast
  79,10,"They say, “Will we be brought back to life"
  79,11,after we have turned into decayed bones?”
  79,12,"They say, “Then that would surely be a losing return!”"
  79,13,It will only be a single Blast
  79,14,then they will immediately be above the ground
  79,15,Has there come to you the story of Moses
  79,16,when his Lord called out to him at the sacred valley of Tuwa
  79,17,"[Saying,] “Go to Pharaoh, for he has transgressed all bounds”"
  79,18,"And say: ‘Are you willing to be purified"
  79,19,and I will guide you to your Lord so that you may fear Him?’”
  79,20,Then Moses showed him the greatest sign
  79,21,But Pharaoh denied it and disobeyed
  79,22,Then he turned back striving to plot
  79,23,"He gathered [his people] and proclaimed"
  79,24,"saying, “I am your lord, the most high.”"
  79,25,So Allah seized him for an exemplary punishment in this life and in the Hereafter
  79,26,"Indeed, there is a lesson in this for those who fear Allah"
  79,27,Are you more difficult to create or the heaven that He built
  79,28,He raised it high and proportioned it
  79,29,and darkened its night and brought forth its daylight
  79,30,And thereafter He spread out the earth
  79,31,brought forth from it its water and its pasture
  79,32,and set the mountains firmly
  79,33,as a provision for you and your grazing livestock
  79,34,But when the Supreme Calamity comes
  79,35,on that Day man will remember all what he did
  79,36,and the Blazing Fire will be exposed for all to see
  79,37,As for those who transgressed
  79,38,and preferred the life of this world
  79,39,the Blazing Fire will be their abode
  79,40,But those who feared standing before their Lord and restrained themselves from evil desires
  79,41,Paradise will surely be their abode
  79,42,"They ask you concerning the Hour, “When will it be?”"
  79,43,How could you possibly mention that
  79,44,Its knowledge rests only with your Lord
  79,45,You are only a warner for those who fear it
  79,46,"On the Day when they see it, it will be as if they had remained [in this world] no more than an evening or a morning"
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,when the blind man came to him
  80,3,How would you know? Perhaps he might be purified
  80,4,or he might take heed and benefit from the reminder
  80,5,But he who was indifferent
  80,6,you give him your full attention
  80,7,although you are not to be blamed if he does not purify himself
  80,8,"But as for the one who came to you striving [for purification]"
  80,9,and he fears Allah
  80,10,you let yourself to be distracted from him
  80,11,No indeed; this is a reminder –
  80,12,so whoever wills may give heed to it –
  80,13,on venerable pages
  80,14,exalted and purified
  80,15,"[preserved] in the hands of angel-scribes"
  80,16,honorable and obedient
  80,17,Woe to man; how ungrateful he is
  80,18,From what did He create him
  80,19,He created him from a drop of semen and proportioned him
  80,20,then He made the way easy for him
  80,21,then He caused him to die and be buried
  80,22,"then when He wills, He will resurrect him"
  80,23,Yet he has not fulfilled what He commanded him
  80,24,Let man consider the food he eats
  80,25,How We poured down rainwater in torrents
  80,26,"and caused the soil to split open [for sprouts]"
  80,27,and cause grains to grow in it
  80,28,as well as grapes and fodder
  80,29,and olive trees and date palms
  80,30,and dense orchards
  80,31,and fruits and grass
  80,32,as provision for you and your livestock
  80,33,But when the Deafening Blast comes
  80,34,on that Day everyone will flee from his sibling
  80,35,and from his mother and father
  80,36,and from his wife and children
  80,37,"On that day, everyone will have enough concern of his own"
  80,38,"On that Day, some faces will be bright"
  80,39,cheerful and rejoicing
  80,40,while other faces will be dust-stained
  80,41,covered in darkness
  80,42,"Such are the disbelievers, the wicked"
  81,1,When the sun is wrapped up in darkness
  81,2,and when the stars are scattered
  81,3,and when the mountains are vanished
  81,4,and when pregnant camels are left unattended
  81,5,and when wild beasts are gathered
  81,6,and when the seas are set on fire
  81,7,and when the souls are sorted
  81,8,and when the baby girl buried alive is asked
  81,9,for what crime she was killed
  81,10,and when records of deeds are spread open
  81,11,and when the sky is stripped away
  81,12,and when the Blazing Fire is flared up
  81,13,and when Paradise is brought near –
  81,14,then every soul will know what it has brought about
  81,15,I swear by the receding stars
  81,16,that rise and hide
  81,17,and by the night as it departs
  81,18,and by the day as it breaks –
  81,19,"Indeed, this [Qur’an] is a word conveyed by a noble angel-messenger"
  81,20,"extremely powerful, highly revered with the Lord of the Throne"
  81,21,"obeyed [by other angels] and moreover, trustworthy"
  81,22,"Your fellow [the Prophet] is not madman"
  81,23,"He indeed saw him [Gabriel] on the clear horizon"
  81,24,"He does not withhold [knowledge of] the unseen"
  81,25,"This [Qur’an] is not the word of an accursed devil"
  81,26,So which way are you going
  81,27,It is but a reminder to the worlds
  81,28,for those among you who wish to take the straight path
  81,29,"But you cannot wish except by the Will of Allah, the Lord of the worlds"
  82,1,When the sky breaks apart
  82,2,"and when the stars fall, scattered"
  82,3,and when the seas burst forth
  82,4,and when the graves are overturned
  82,5,then each soul will come to know what it has done or what it has left undone
  82,6,"O mankind, what has lured you away from your Lord, the Most Generous"
  82,7,"Who created you, then shaped and proportioned you"
  82,8,and assembled you in whatever form He willed
  82,9,No indeed; but you deny the Judgment Day
  82,10,while there are watchers over you
  82,11,honorable scribes
  82,12,who know whatever you do
  82,13,"Indeed, the righteous will be in Bliss"
  82,14,and the wicked will be in the Blazing Fire
  82,15,which they will enter on Judgment Day
  82,16,and will never come out of it
  82,17,How do you know what Judgment Day is
  82,18,"Again, how do you know what Judgment Day is"
  82,19,"It is the Day when no soul will be of any help to another, and all command on that Day will be with Allah"
  83,1,Woe to the defrauders
  83,2,those who take full measure when they take from others
  83,3,but they give less when they measure or weigh for them
  83,4,Do they really not think that they will be resurrected
  83,5,for a momentous Day
  83,6,a Day when people will stand before the Lord of the worlds
  83,7,No indeed! The record of the wicked is surely in Sijjīn
  83,8,How do you know what Sijjīn is
  83,9,It is a clearly inscribed Record
  83,10,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  83,11,those who deny the Judgment Day
  83,12,None denies it except every sinful transgressor
  83,13,"When Our verses are recited to him, he says, “Ancient fables!”"
  83,14,No indeed! Their hearts have been stained by what they used to commit
  83,15,No indeed! On that Day they will be barred from seeing their Lord
  83,16,They will then surely enter the Blazing Fire
  83,17,"then they will be told, “This is what you used to deny.”"
  83,18,No indeed! The record of the righteous is certainly in ‘illiyyīn –
  83,19,and how do you know what ‘illiyyūn is? –
  83,20,It is a record inscribed
  83,21,witnessed by those who are close to Allah
  83,22,"Indeed, the righteous will be in Bliss"
  83,23,"seated on the couches, gazing in wonder"
  83,24,You will see on their faces the radiance of bliss
  83,25,They will be served to drink pure wine from a sealed container
  83,26,"whose last sip is musk – let those who strive, strive for that –"
  83,27,and it will be mixed with water from the spring of Tasnīm
  83,28,a spring from which those who are close to Allah will drink
  83,29,"Indeed, the wicked used to laugh at the believers"
  83,30,"when they passed by them, they would wink at one another"
  83,31,"and when they went back to their people, they would return exulting"
  83,32,"When they saw the believers, they would say, “These people are truly misguided,”"
  83,33,although they were not sent as their keepers
  83,34,So Today the believers will laugh at the disbelievers
  83,35,"while sitting on the couches, gazing around"
  83,36,Have the disbelievers been rewarded except for what they used to do
  84,1,When the sky is rent asunder
  84,2,"and hearkens to its Lord, as it must"
  84,3,and when the earth is leveled out
  84,4,"and casts out all what it contains, and becomes empty"
  84,5,"and hearkens to its Lord, as it must"
  84,6,"O humans, you are toiling towards your Lord, and you will surely meet Him"
  84,7,Whoever is given his Record in his right hand
  84,8,he will have an easy reckoning
  84,9,and he will return to his people joyfully
  84,10,But whoever is given his Record from behind his back
  84,11,he will call out for destruction
  84,12,and he will enter the Blazing Fire
  84,13,"Indeed, he used to live among his people joyfully"
  84,14,"and he thought that he would never return [to Allah]"
  84,15,Indeed he will! His Lord was always watching him
  84,16,"Indeed, I swear by the twilight"
  84,17,and by the night and what it covers
  84,18,and by the moon when it becomes full
  84,19,You will surely pass from one stage to another
  84,20,Then what is the matter with them that they do not believe
  84,21,"and when the Qur’an is recited to them, they do not prostrate"
  84,22,"Rather, the disbelievers persist in denying it"
  84,23,but Allah knows best whatever they harbor in their hearts
  84,24,So give them the tidings of a painful punishment
  84,25,But those who believe and do righteous deeds will have a never-ending reward
  85,1,By the sky full of constellations
  85,2,and by the promised Day
  85,3,and by the witness and the witnessed
  85,4,cursed be the makers of the trench
  85,5,the fire full of fuel
  85,6,when they sat around it
  85,7,and were witnessing what they did to the believers
  85,8,"Their only grievance against them was that they believed in Allah, the All-Mighty, the Praiseworthy"
  85,9,"to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth, and Allah is Witness over all things"
  85,10,"Indeed, for those who tortured the believing men and women, then did not repent, there will be the punishment of Hell and the punishment of the burning fire"
  85,11,But those who believed and did righteous deeds will certainly have gardens under which rivers flow; that is the supreme triumph
  85,12,"Indeed, the punishment of your Lord is severe"
  85,13,"Indeed, it is He Who originates [the creation] then repeats it"
  85,14,"and He is the All-Forgiving, the Most Affectionate"
  85,15,the Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,He does whatever He wills
  85,17,Has there not come to you the story of the forces
  85,18,of Pharaoh and Thamūd
  85,19,But the disbelievers are in persistent denial
  85,20,although Allah encompasses them from all sides
  85,21,But this is a glorious Qur’an
  85,22,"[inscribed] in a Preserved Tablet"
  86,1,By the sky and the night comer –
  86,2,and how do you know what the night comer is
  86,3,It is the star of piercing brightness –
  86,4,there is no soul except that there is a watcher over it
  86,5,Let man reflect on what he was created from
  86,6,He was created from a spurting fluid
  86,7,emerging from between the backbone and the ribs
  86,8,"Indeed, Allah is able to bring him back to life"
  86,9,On the Day when all secrets will be disclosed
  86,10,"he will then have no power, nor any helper"
  86,11,By the sky and its recurring rain
  86,12,"and by the earth that cracks open [with the sprout of plants]"
  86,13,"Indeed, this [Qur’an] is a decisive word"
  86,14,which is not for amusement
  86,15,"Indeed, they are devising a plan"
  86,16,I am too devising a plan
  86,17,"So bear with the disbelievers, and respite them for a while"
  87,1,"Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,Who created and fashioned in due proportion
  87,3,"and Who determined [the creation] then guided them"
  87,4,and Who brings forth the pasture
  87,5,then makes it into withered chaff
  87,6,"We will teach you [the Qur’an], so you will not forget"
  87,7,"except what Allah wills, for indeed He knows what is manifest and what is hidden"
  87,8,We will guide you to the easy way
  87,9,"So remind, if the reminder should benefit"
  87,10,He who fears Allah will take heed
  87,11,but the wretched will avoid it
  87,12,who will enter the Great Fire
  87,13,wherein he will neither die nor live
  87,14,"Indeed, he who purifies himself will attain success"
  87,15,and remembers his Lord’s Name and prays
  87,16,But you prefer the life of this world
  87,17,even though the Hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,"Indeed, this was in the earlier Scriptures"
  87,19,the Scriptures of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Has there come to you the story of the Overwhelming Event
  88,2,"On that Day, some faces will be humiliated"
  88,3,toiling and weary
  88,4,as they burn in a scorching Fire
  88,5,They will be made to drink from a boiling spring
  88,6,and they will have no food except bitter thorny plants
  88,7,that neither nourishes nor satisfies hunger
  88,8,Other faces on that Day will be joyful
  88,9,well-pleased with their past striving
  88,10,in an elevated garden
  88,11,wherein no idle talk will be heard
  88,12,There will be a flowing spring
  88,13,and couches raised high
  88,14,and cups placed ready
  88,15,and cushions lined up
  88,16,and splendid carpets spread out
  88,17,"Do they not reflect on the camel, how it is created"
  88,18,"and the sky, how it is raised high"
  88,19,"and the mountains, how they are firmly set up"
  88,20,"and the earth, how it is spread out"
  88,21,"So remind [O Prophet]; your duty is only to remind"
  88,22,you are not assigned to compel them
  88,23,But whoever turns away and disbelieves
  88,24,Allah will inflict upon him the greatest punishment
  88,25,"Indeed, to Us is their return"
  88,26,then it is for Us to call them to account
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and the ten nights
  89,3,and the even and the odd
  89,4,and by the night when it comes
  89,5,are these oaths not sufficient for those who have sense
  89,6,Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with ‘Ād
  89,7,"of Iram, who were people of great stature"
  89,8,the like of whom had never been created in the land
  89,9,"and Thamūd, who carved out the rocks in the Valley"
  89,10,and the mighty and powerful Pharaoh
  89,11,All of them transgressed in the land
  89,12,and spread therein much corruption
  89,13,so your Lord poured upon them a scourge of punishment
  89,14,"Indeed, your Lord is ever vigilant"
  89,15,"As for man, when he is tested by his Lord by honoring him and bestowing blessings upon him, he says, “My Lord has [deservedly] honored me!”"
  89,16,"But when he is tested by restricting his provision, he says, “My Lord has [undeservedly] humiliated me!”"
  89,17,No indeed! You are not kind to the orphan
  89,18,nor do you urge one another to feed the needy
  89,19,and you greedily consume the entire inheritance
  89,20,and love wealth immensely
  89,21,No indeed! When the earth is crushed over and over
  89,22,"and your Lord comes with the angels, rank after rank"
  89,23,"and Hell is brought near on that Day – this is when man will understand, but what is the use of that understanding"
  89,24,"He will say, “Would that I had sent forth something for my [eternal] life!”"
  89,25,None can punish as He punishes on that Day
  89,26,and none can bind as He binds
  89,27,"[It will be said to the believer,] “O the tranquil soul"
  89,28,"Return to your Lord, well pleased and pleasing [to Him]"
  89,29,"Join My [righteous] slaves"
  89,30,and enter My Paradise.”
  90,1,"I do swear by this city [of Makkah] –"
  90,2,"and you are free of restriction [for a while] in this city –"
  90,3,and by every parent and offspring
  90,4,We have created man in hardship
  90,5,Does he think that none can ever have power over him
  90,6,"He says, “I have squandered enormous wealth!”"
  90,7,Does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Have We not given him two eyes
  90,9,and a tongue and two lips
  90,10,"and shown him the two ways [of right and wrong]"
  90,11,Yet he did not make his way through the steep path
  90,12,and how do you know what the steep path is
  90,13,It is freeing a slave
  90,14,or giving food on a day of hunger
  90,15,to an orphan relative
  90,16,or to a needy person in misery
  90,17,"then [most importantly] to be one of those who believe and exhort one another to patience and exhort one another to compassion"
  90,18,Such are the people of the Right
  90,19,"As for those who reject Our signs, they are the people of the Left"
  90,20,who will be locked up in the Fire
  91,1,By the sun and its brightness
  91,2,and by the moon as it follows it
  91,3,and by the day as it displays it
  91,4,and by the night as it covers it
  91,5,and by the sky and how He made it
  91,6,and by the earth and how He spread it
  91,7,and by the soul and how He fashioned it
  91,8,"then inspired it [to know] its wickedness and righteousness"
  91,9,"Indeed, he who purifies his soul will attain success"
  91,10,and he who corrupts it will be doomed
  91,11,"Thamūd rejected [the messenger] because of their transgression"
  91,12,"when the most wretched among them rose [to kill the camel]"
  91,13,"Although the messenger of Allah warned them, “Hands off the she-camel of Allah and her drink!”"
  91,14,Yet they rejected him and hamstrung her. So their Lord destroyed them for their sin and leveled them to the ground
  91,15,And He has no fear of the consequences thereof
  92,1,By the night when it covers
  92,2,and by the day when it appears
  92,3,and by His creation of male and female
  92,4,surely your efforts are divergent
  92,5,As for the one who gives in charity and fears Allah
  92,6,and truly believes in the best reward
  92,7,We will make easy for him the way of salvation
  92,8,But as for the one who is miserly and deems himself self-sufficient
  92,9,and denies the best reward
  92,10,We will make easy for him the way of perdition
  92,11,"His wealth will be of no avail to him when he tumbles [into Hell]"
  92,12,"Indeed, it is upon Us to show the right way"
  92,13,and surely to Us belong the Hereafter and the present life
  92,14,So I warn you of a raging Fire
  92,15,none will enter it except the most wretched
  92,16,who denied and turned away
  92,17,But the most righteous will be saved from it
  92,18,who spends his wealth to purify himself
  92,19,not in return for someone’s favors
  92,20,"but to seek the pleasure of his Lord, the Most High"
  92,21,He will surely be well pleased
  93,1,By the morning brightness
  93,2,and by the night when it is still
  93,3,"your Lord has not forsaken you [O Prophet], nor does He hate you"
  93,4,the Hereafter is better for you than the present life
  93,5,and your Lord will certainly give you so much that you will be well pleased
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan then take good care of you
  93,7,Did He not find you unguided then guide you
  93,8,Did He not find you in need then enrich you
  93,9,So do not mistreat the orphan
  93,10,nor repulse the beggar
  93,11,and proclaim the blessings of your Lord
  94,1,"Have We not reassured your heart for you [O Prophet]"
  94,2,and relieved you of your burden
  94,3,that weighed down your back
  94,4,and raised high your fame for you
  94,5,"For indeed, with hardship comes ease"
  94,6,"indeed, with hardship comes ease"
  94,7,"So whenever you are free, strive in worship"
  94,8,and turn to your Lord in devotion
  95,1,"By the fig and the olive [of Jerusalem]"
  95,2,"and by Mount Sinai [of Egypt]"
  95,3,"and by this secure city [of Makkah]"
  95,4,Surely We have created man in the best form
  95,5,then We will reduce him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,except those who believe and do righteous deeds; they will have a never-ending reward
  95,7,"Then, what makes you deny the Judgment Day"
  95,8,Is not Allah the Most Just of all judges
  96,1,Read in the name of your Lord Who created
  96,2,created man from a clinging clot
  96,3,"Read, and your Lord is the Most Generous"
  96,4,Who taught by the pen
  96,5,taught man what he did not know
  96,6,"Indeed, man transgresses"
  96,7,when he deems himself to be self-sufficient
  96,8,"Indeed, to your Lord is the return"
  96,9,Have you seen the one who prevents
  96,10,"a slave [of Allah] from praying"
  96,11,"What if this [slave] is rightly guided"
  96,12,and enjoins righteousness
  96,13,How about the one who denies and turns away
  96,14,Does he not know that Allah is watching all
  96,15,"No indeed; if he does not desist, We will surely drag him by the forelock –"
  96,16,"a lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,So let him call his associates
  96,18,We will call the wardens of Hellfire
  96,19,"No indeed; do not obey him, but prostrate and draw near [to Allah]"
  97,1,"Indeed, We sent this [Qur’an] down in the Night of Decree"
  97,2,How do you know what the Night of Decree is
  97,3,The Night of Decree is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"On that night the angels and the Spirit [Gabriel] descend by their Lord’s permission with all decrees"
  97,5,It is all peace until the break of dawn
  98,1,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists were not going to desist [from disbelief] until there came to them clear proof"
  98,2,"a messenger from Allah, reciting pure pages"
  98,3,containing upright commandments
  98,4,Yet those who were given the Scripture did not disagree except after the clear proof came to them
  98,5,"although they were commanded only to worship Allah with sincere devotion to Him, being inclined to true faith, and to establish prayer and give zakah; that is the true religion"
  98,6,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists will be in the fire of Hell, abiding therein forever. It is they who are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,As for those who believe and do righteous deeds – it is they who are the best of creatures
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord is Gardens of Eternity under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. This is for those who fear their Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is shaken with a mighty quake
  99,2,and the earth throws out its burdens
  99,3,"and man says, “What is the matter with it?”"
  99,4,On that Day it will recount all its news
  99,5,"because your Lord has inspired it [to do so]"
  99,6,On that Day all people will come forward in separate groups to be shown their deeds
  99,7,So whoever does an atom’s weight of good will see it
  99,8,and whoever does an atom’s weight of evil will see it
  100,1,"By the galloping, panting horses"
  100,2,"striking sparks of fire [with their hooves]"
  100,3,launching raids at dawn
  100,4,stirring up thereby clouds of dust
  100,5,plunging thereby into the midst of the enemy
  100,6,"indeed, man is very ungrateful to his Lord –"
  100,7,and he himself is a witness to that –
  100,8,and he is truly extreme in his love of wealth
  100,9,Does he not know that the contents of graves will be overturned
  100,10,and the secrets of the hearts will be brought to light
  100,11,"Indeed, their Lord is All-Aware of them on that Day"
  101,1,The Striking Calamity
  101,2,What is the Striking Calamity
  101,3,How do you know what the Striking Calamity is
  101,4,On that Day people will be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains will be like carded wool
  101,6,Then the one whose scales of good deeds are heavy
  101,7,will have a pleasant life
  101,8,But the one whose scales of good deeds are light
  101,9,his abode will be the abyss
  101,10,And how do you know what it is
  101,11,It is a Blazing Fire
  102,1,"Competition for worldly gains distracts you [from Allah]"
  102,2,until you come to your graves
  102,3,No indeed! You will come to know
  102,4,Again no! You will come to know
  102,5,No indeed! If only you knew for certain
  102,6,You will surely see the Blazing Fire
  102,7,"Again, you will see it with absolute certainty"
  102,8,Then on that Day you will surely be asked about your worldly pleasures
  103,1,By the time
  103,2,man is in utter loss
  103,3,"except those who believe and do righteous deeds, and exhort one another to the truth and exhort one another to patience"
  104,1,Woe to every backbiter and slanderer
  104,2,who amasses wealth and counts it over and again
  104,3,thinking that his wealth will make him live forever
  104,4,No indeed! He will surely be cast into the Crushing Fire
  104,5,and how do you know what the Crushing Fire is
  104,6,It is the kindled Fire of Allah
  104,7,which reaches the hearts
  104,8,It will be closed down upon them
  104,9,locked with towering columns
  105,1,Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with the people of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not turn their scheme into a total loss
  105,3,He sent against them swarms of birds
  105,4,pelting them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,leaving them like chewed up and trampled chaff
  106,1,For the accustomed security of Quraysh
  106,2,secure in their winter and summer journeys
  106,3,"Let them worship the Lord of this [Sacred] House"
  106,4,Who fed them against hunger and made them secure against fear
  107,1,Have you seen the one who denies the Recompense
  107,2,Such is the one who repulses the orphan harshly
  107,3,and does not urge others to feed the needy
  107,4,So woe to those who pray
  107,5,but are heedless of their prayer
  107,6,those who only show off
  107,7,and withhold even the small kindnesses
  108,1,"We have surely given you [O Prophet] Al-Kauthar [abundance]"
  108,2,so pray and sacrifice to your Lord alone
  108,3,"Indeed, the one who hates you is truly cut off [from all goodness]"
  109,1,"Say, “O disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,nor do you worship what I worship
  109,4,Never will I worship what you worship
  109,5,nor will you ever worship what I worship
  109,6,You have your religion and I have my religion
  110,1,When there comes Allah’s help and the conquest
  110,2,and you see people entering Allah’s religion in multitudes
  110,3,"then glorify the praise of your Lord, and ask His forgiveness. Indeed, He is ever Accepting of Repentance"
  111,1,"May the hands of Abu Lahab perish, and may he perish"
  111,2,Neither his wealth nor his worldly gains will avail him
  111,3,He will burn in a Flaming Fire
  111,4,"and so will his wife, the carrier of firewood"
  111,5,around her neck will be a rope of palm fiber
  112,1,"Say: He is Allah, the One"
  112,2,"Allah, the Eternal Refuge"
  112,3,He neither begets nor is He begotten
  112,4,and there is none comparable to Him.”
  113,1,"Say, “I seek refuge with the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the harm of all what He has created
  113,3,from the harm of night’s darkness when it spreads around
  113,4,from the harm of the sorceresses who blow on knots
  113,5,and from the harm of the envier when he envies
  114,1,"Say, “I seek refuge with the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,the Sovereign of mankind
  114,3,the God of mankind
  114,4,from the harm of the lurking whisperer
  114,5,who whispers into the hearts of mankind
  114,6,from among jinn and mankind.”